{"text": "THE GOOD: Such an incredible game. I got it to relive the nostalgia of back when I had it for the Xbox 360 and it's just as fun as I remembered it to be. The combat is very fluid and switching guns is very satisfying. Also Alicia's dodge moves are really cool. Your magic abilities you get are very fun too. You can shoot down bolts of lightning, create tornadoes, or melt dudes with meteor showers. All of the guns are OP like the GATLING GUN!!! and very fun to use the element upgrade to either give them elemental damage like lightning, fire, etc. I was really emotionally attached to the characters and the story though. Alicia is such a likable character and it is interesting how every time you play the game more, you uncover more and more about her dark past. THE BAD: Lots of invisible walls. During this game you will have to destroy things that are creating these walls A LOT. It gets a bit repetitive when you have to kill a thing, unlock a wall, run all the way back to where the wall is, just to realize that there is a different wall right in front of you and you gotta now go run off and kill a different thing. So a lot of running back and forth. Also I felt like the other characters were a bit bland, and the game could have had more dialogues between Alicia and the other characters. Oh, and SNIPERS ARE SOO ANNOYING, like they can insta you from across the map. It's like a COD multiplayer game with hackers. So you gotta take those suckers out when you see them ASAP. Overall I thought this was a solid game. If you can handle all of these old 2006 graphics and a damn fun game then this game is for you. This game is better than Bayonetta hands down >_<", "appid": "696180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082425835", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "18", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574510400.0}
