{"text": "Simple Machines is a part puzzle, part quick reaction game where your job is to guide one or more balls through increasingly more complex 2D mazes. Levels start pretty easy, rotate a platform up or down by clicking on it to allow the ball to fall but new ways to change the trajectory of the ball are introduced often. Jump the balls, carry them on moving platforms, open and shut platforms, switches, speed boosts, rotating elements that can catch the ball and more.  Later levels also include grey objects and balls that instantly kill your balls should they come into contact with them. Like a lot of the $1 minimalist puzzle games, itâ€™s 4/5ths tutorial and 1/5th of the best challenging levels. I do wish some games would include more of these challenging levels as they are really quite good and a few of them demand very precise timing and when you get it right there is a definite feeling of accomplishment. The sound and visuals are great across all 80 levels and for the price asked the 2 hours or so are well spent, it just needs some more complex levels as thatâ€™s where the game really shines.", "appid": "1307850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021940873", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591963200.0}
