{"text": "After player Half-Life 1 long ago and playing the mod version of Black Mesa some time ago, I've decided to purchase Black Mesa to further help  support development for this game. I find it funny how this game is more buggier than the mod. There are textures that's phasing in and out from the textures behind the texture, AI is act weird and sometimes don't work at all, glitches on the trams where it kicks you off, and other bugs that's currently present in this game. However, most or all bugs in this game is noticeable, but can be ignored as it doesn't inflict much of an impact on your progression in your game. Other than that, never before have I felt in love with a remake before in my life. A true love letter to the fans of the Half-Life Community.  Graphically and atmospherically, the game is beautiful. The lightning and the music and graphic design is all beautiful, and that was when I was inside Black Mesa. Into XEN, it was breath taking to view such an ecosystem inside a game such as this. It was astonishing to see all the creatures, the entire outer world of Xen and what it has to offer to everyone's eyes. It's such an alien world that's difficult to explain. If you're a fan of Half-Life or want to get into Half-Life, I truly recommend Black Mesa to anyone.", "appid": "362890", "steamid": "profiles/76561197994567639", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1578052800.0}
