{"text": "Ok, my third review for the special edition, because I wasn't really happy and was able to play more. And sorry for my bad english, I use my expandable english and google translate :D I received this edition for free, because I already have the normal version with all the DLC's and I loved the game and spent many hours in Skyrim. Therefore, I recommend the regular version definitely, but is it the same with the special edition?  I would say maybe.  -Short charging times due to the 64-bit Engine -The new lighting effects look very good -no stuttering when changing the current Cell -Everything is generally more colorful and mostly realistic illuminated -Dynamic Focus The rest hasn't changed too hard. The quests are the same, the faces are still emotionless ( :D ), bugs were take...  All in all it is ok, but not awesome. If you played the normal version with mods, that isn't a big upgrade for you... But it is still Skyrim, in my view the best game of all time, therefore I recommend it logically. The feeling is still awesome!  Best regards EL inus", "appid": "489830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198191907538", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1477828800.0}
