{"text": "So I've pumped 50 hours into this game, 200+ hours into PUBG, 100+ hours in BO4 Black out mode and 50+ hours into Fortnite and overall as a Battle royal style game it has its ups and downs. All I see is people complaining about the privacy risks and to be fair I dont mind these 'risks' since most other games do the same thing or something similar. If you want to grope and cry about a game it should be CSGO ever since it went free to play since hackers/exploiters can keep coming back over and over again. Ring of elysium My verdict: The game is a bit slow at times and I'm happy they put 1st/3rd person modes in since PUBG took months to do this. It does seem like a lot more balanced in terms of weapons against games like fortnite where everything is broken when they do an update. As a battle royal game I really like Ring of elysium. Its fun to play with friends and the whole twist of winning makes the game more on edge for players since 4 random people can win. I do think the recoil on some guns is a bit too high like the famas but overall I really enjoy this game.  A game where you choose where you spawn and choose 1 of 3 mobility items whether it be the snowboard, Glider or ice picks is an awesome addition to the Battle royal genre.  Definitely rate this game! The event mode is a bit weird since it keeps coming off and on. Servers can be a bit wonky too sometimes. (Only gripes I have)", "appid": "755790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198278318680", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1543579200.0}
