{"text": "Well, I think it's time to update this review. After more than 3000 hours I can say that this game can provide the most value out of any other game I have ever played. Why? Well besides the fact the game is free it's also incredibly fun to play, no other game has the goofiness and in many cases the share stupidity you can encounter on both on official and non-official servers. Just to name a few: 'The pootis Bird', the banjo spamming mosquito engineer, spy crabs, demopans and so many more things you can see in the badlands. Apart from the fun and never the same game-play this game also has the trading aspect.  Trading has without a doubt changed the way I talk to people and look at the world. It allowed me to afford things I never thought I could, meet tons, of some of the most incredible people and make connections which lasted for years and of course allowed me to get the shiny hats I always wanted. And frankly.. You can do it too! Thru trial and error, you can also build your trading empire! Besides all of that, there is the community which is probably one of the most dedicated groups of people I have ever seen. All of the SFM creators, Youtubers (these guys don't always stay with us for long), the mod makers and finally the players, all of these people make up what is tf2 and keep it alive! To summarise, this game is arguably the best game I've been introduced too, it brings incredible value to the table, no pay to win, the feeling of community, trading, fun. And it's free, so give it a shot and you won't look back! And yes - 'Tf2 is truly a timeless masterpiece'.  Thanks and Have a wonderful day - I'll see you on the battlefield! Justin.", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198153088409", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479384000.0}
