{"text": "Personally, i didnt have any problems with the remastered Version. Ran 60 FPS smooth and clean with no crashes all through my 18 hours playtime. (GTX 770, i5 4670) As someone who played the original on console, coming back to this version on PC is really not that bad. But i can see the critic in this \"remastered\" Version. I wouldn't consider it a full remaster aswell, the changes from the original are rather small and the thing that bothered me the most were the sounds, which were partly just copied from the original in their rather bad quality, but all around i think its just a bit more polished and clean than the original. If you dont have any performance issues it is just a better game, i also didn't encounter a single bug. And lets not forget, most of us got this game for free. But if it wouldnt be for that, and i had to pay 20 Bucks for that i would probaly say : get the original. The changes arent worth the price and you get pretty much the same experience.", "appid": "409710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198141206700", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1474977600.0}
