{"text": "Even if you have to wait for 400 days to finish the game properly, there are legit ways to do it faster, so it's sadly shorter â€“ and I mean sadly, because the exploration is really soothing and the character and setting of the game are so as well! As of writing this review, I've yet to finish the game, but I have sadly explored most of it during my ~20 hours of play, though it will be longer if you won't read the guide, as some puzzles require challenge to figuring out. Generally, I relly recommend it, and I hope for more games following a similar pattern to this game :) As far As playing on Linux goes, it it native, it works great, it's based on Unity 5 and uses OpenGL by default, but the Vulkan version can be forced using \"-force-vulkan\" switch. Sadly there's no native Wayland support in Unity 5, but it's buggy in newer Unity games anyway, and Steam as well as various game-related utilities still rely on X11, so it doesn't matter. If you don't want to stress your GPU, you also need to limit the framerate with an external tool, as the game uses all it have available to render as many frames as possible. I sometimes gets some small hangs for a second or so, but it may be because I play on Vulkan, XWayland, have the framerate capped to 60 through MangoHud and/or I don't use a kernel optimized for gaming at this moment.", "appid": "893850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198001116101", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585396800.0}
