{"text": "You have more than likely played this game before, it exists on most platforms with the title being any combination of the words 'Game' 'Dev' 'Developer' 'Maker' and/or 'Tycoon'. It's an easy enough game to pick up, never really gets that challenging but fo rthe most part it remains entertaining. I hate the monthly reports popping up and screwing up the flow of te game, if I am fast forwarding three games through development I don't need to have everything come to a screeching halt so I can click to close the popup. You can hire real devs in the game which is a nice touch, I hired Molyneux to head up a game's release but it never came out, kinda like Fable Legends. Cheap game, fun and definitely worth a pick up if you like this type of game.", "appid": "399670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090169065", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1469793600.0}
