{"text": "I'd consider this a successor to my previous favorite MMO of all time which was Anarchy Online, there's quite a few similarities between them but since AO is no longer updated and PSO2 still is and has meaningful content and more, it comes out on top. This is a more traditional hub-based action MMO, while you won't need a trifecta of tank/healer/DPS, you will need some support along with massive amounts of damage and enough sense to keep some people alive/not in much danger so they can revive/heal others so the entire group doesn't wipe. There's a real sense of community, for instance, in Ship 1 Block 1 in Franca's Cafe you can meet a lot of chill people who visit there each day as well as Block 69 pretty much anywhere since that's the most populated block of Ship 1 with all the regulars/veterans(beware M/Ao-rated content in Block 69). While there's grind, it's not bad. I never felt like I was grinding while getting to the next stages, except probably near levels 60-70 when I was trying to unlock the last bit of content that unlocks at 70 since I had obtained some pretty overpowered gear at that point and was practically destroying my-level content, got hard again real fast after 70 though, so no issue there... Overall, far less grindy than something like Maplestory but there isn't a clear-cut path if you wanna speedrun from say 1-80 in a day like you can go to max level easily in World of Warcraft. You get 3 recommended quests a day and tons of daily quests, you probably won't run out of quests to do in a day if you keep accepting and doing the content but the meaningful amount of EXP you get from those quests drops hard around level 50 and doesn't end up scaling higher, weekly and daily 'missions' will give a fair bit of EXP and meseta(currency) though. The maps for each area are randomly generated but similar to Diablo 2 there's a general direction you can usually head in to find yourself at the exit, or at your goal. The random emergency quests or random encounters you'll find will differ with each run too except for in Time Attack Quests which run on the same seed each run. The randomly generated quest system keeps each map run unique and lets you rerun the same map multiple times without getting bored, especially since those random encounters can collide, and not just 2x, but sometimes even 3x or more causing some truly epic and hard battles that you weren't expecting to just appear out of thin air. Even if you play by yourself without inviting a friend to join you, as long as you have active recruitment on you can add NPC allies to your team based off players who submitted their \"Friend Avatar\" and they will use the same skills as those players and other players can hop in and take the slot of one of those NPCs (only if you have Active Recruitment on which you toggle when accepting a quest). People will join very often and the game feels very alive even though it's a hub-based quest accepting game where you go directly to the location, many areas are multi-party areas with 12 people and especially recommended quests and high-end areas you will always meet and fight alongside others. The NPC ally system also allows you to play truly solo if that's your jam and you just want to relax and go at the quests at your own pace, just don't expect them to fare too well in the true level 80 content like Ultimate Quests, where you'd at most want to bring one Techter(support class) alongside you to be a buff-slave with active recruitment on so someone can take that slot eventually. Character Creation is god-tier, you can create any character of your dreams and there's always collaborations going on such as the newly added Persona collab which added costume pieces from persona 3-5, as well as music tracks for your own personal quarters and emotes for the 3 different methods of summoning personas and the dances done in their dance spin-off games.  The only thing I can find to dislike about this game is if you happen to be a truly free-to-play player and never pay a dime then inventory management may be an issue. It's worth noting that if you don't buy the premium subscription (about $13 USD a month) then you also can't trade with other players or use certain pre-quest buffs. None of that is really game-breaking though as the rate at which you find items is fairly good and you're looking more at Guild Wars 2 exotic-drop rates for high-tier items and not top-tier mythical raid drop rates like in World of WarCraft. Currently the game only goes to Episode 4 whereas the Japanese release is on Episode 6 so the highest tier gear you can find is 14* but it's incredibly rare as there's not much content it drops from out yet and your only shots are certain urgent quests which only occur for 30 minutes at a time, however 13* items are aplenty in extremely hard missions and ultimate quests. If you have the money to spend for the premium pass and a few inventory expansions I'd rate this game 10/10, otherwise I could see that free-to-play players might have issues with the inventory system which may or may not be game breaking depending on the type of gamer you are. Inventory passes last forever though so if you treat the game as a one time purchase of $35 for the 10 inventory expansions, or realistically you could go for $21 worth and still be fine, then I'd still give it a 10/10... I would probably not advise going full free-to-play to be perfectly honest.", "appid": "1056640", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968151160", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597579200.0}
{"text": "The game is quite simple and self explanatory and really fast to play through, it didnt take me ( and every one else) much more than 30-40mins to complete it.  Nontheless it was surprisingly much fun to play and you get over 100 easy achievements. So perfect for all the achievement hunters out there. On top you even get some cards. Overall its a perfect game for all the achievement hunters and people that want perfect (aka 100% games) and dont have a lot of time or patience", "appid": "533300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091406307", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1483099200.0}
