{"text": "======================================================================= New review after completing the game: It's great... it's not perfect, but it does what it strives to do nicely: - choice matters - story is solid and faithful to the movies (especially to the first 2, lots of references in-game) - decent gameplay mechanics - overall polished experience (I encountered 0 bug throughout my gameplay) - the terminator vibe is there However, there are 2 things that I would deemed as it's biggest downside: - The budget constraint (facial animation, graphical quality, etc) - Short story length + almost 0% replayability (story-wise)... probably had to do with the first reason too Credit where credits due... A passion project, full of ambition like this, despite its flaws, deserves support... And if you're a fan of Terminator series (especially the first 2 movies), I wholeheartedly recommend you give this game a try at least for now... Hope the devs came back with even better games in the future", "appid": "954740", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130915920", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573819200.0}
