{"text": "I've never given much thought of this game as it looked like another one of those mobile games to me, started playing out of curiosity, and I'm hooked. Albion feels like a true MMORPG where there's a huge amount of player freedom and it doesn't have the \"on rails\" feel that the other popular MMO's have. I like the fact that you can set your own goals and work towards them on your own terms, and once your craft that piece of gear, it feels rewarding and I like the concept of  \"you are what you wear\". As for the performance, the game runs amazingly well on my modest PC even when there are a ton of players on the screen. I understand that the servers are located in US but I (as a player connecting from South Asia) have't had any de-syncs, ability delays or rubber banding issues so far. Highly recommend.", "appid": "761890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066728245", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593345600.0}
