{"text": "My impressions so far. It's a fun game, simply put. The fighting is pretty spot on, and each time you get hit or hit the other, it's incredibly satisfying thanks to feedback and the excellent sound design. The graphics are smooth and what you'd expect from a game on the Unreal engine. The models can look a little odd, but you can easily look past that. The character roster is great in my opinion, and I seriously look forward to the release of DLC characters. Now... This game isn't perfect. Far from it. It's obvious most of the budget went into the fighting mechanics. The story is rather lacking... Specifically the cutscenes and some animations. I get some serious MVC Infinite vibes with how the characters move. They move like the characters in the Food Fight movie. The character's mouths are also pretty terrible when they're speaking. The walking and running animations for your avatar and others are also pretty bad. However, there's one thing that just flabbergasts me... THEY DIDN'T GIVE RYUK A VOICE ACTOR. He has lines in the cutscenes, and he flails around as if he was talking, but there's no sound that comes from him. How the hell did that happen? In the end, it's not a game for everyday people. It's niche like most anime games. But, if you like Shonen, and you like fighting games, you'll enjoy this as well.", "appid": "816020", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051618139", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550145600.0}
