{"text": "Just finished the campaign. I wouldn't say its my favorite Ace Combat game, but its definitely a good, if not great, one. That said, I do have a few complaints. First off, the HUD is a bit too light of a color and turns practically invisible at times when clouds are in front of you. If there is a way to change the color, I didn't find it. Secondly, the Annahilation missions are meh. I'd rather have some objectives than just trying to get a certain score in 20 or so minutes. Additionally, in some ways I felt that it took a step back from Ace Combat 6. Operations kept things different for each mission, adding replay value and made the battlefield seem more alive. The AI in this game is also rather lackluster. While I can ultimately live with the incompetence of non-wingmen, I wish ordering wingmates to Attack or Cover you was back and not being able to choose their loadouts was also a disappointment. Lastly, I wish there were more multiplayer modes. While I have been enjoying the current modes, I would love to see Coop and Objective-based modes. Not only would this add more to do, I'm sure this would get quite a few more people into the Multiplayer (I've seen a few disinterested in the basic FFA and TDM modes). Despite these complaints, though, I want to stress that this is easily a must play for any Ace Combat fans and if I was faced with the choice to buy it again knowing what I know now, I wouldn't hesitate for a second.", "appid": "502500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198058577590", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549022400.0}
