{"text": "Pretty epic single player experience, especially with mods. Would completely recommend this game, especially at its current price of $30. My views on Online are currently mixed, as much as I want to enjoy it, I simply just can't. It's so disappointing to see what Rockstar has implented into this game. The amount of micro transactions and online DLC in Online is nothing short of ridiculous. The community is also pretty stinky. To avoid the community I would advise you find a couple of friends and play in a private session. The heists in Online are incredibly engaging when you have friends to play with.  Other than the interaction of friends, there really are no pros of Online. Social Club is also very stinky. Hopefully RDR2 won't have the same problems but it probably will.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198202850698", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541851200.0}
