{"text": "Some very annoying problems hold this back from being an amazing game. Instead its a good game. These problems are: hidden timers that can lock you into a game fail-state, *extreme* difficulty spikes, and the kingdom management in general. Supposedly the developer fixed the fail-state loops, where if you neglected the primary quests the hidden timer would result in you not having enough time to complete them, thereby causing you to lose the game. They also said they fixed the end-game difficulty, but I never played it until the mega patch was released. I found the end game to be absurdly difficult, with ridiculously OP enemies, and possible permanent loss of your favorite characters. Toward the end I was completely fatigued with the game and just wanted it to be over with. It's worth playing.", "appid": "640820", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975698109", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0}
