{"text": "It's a fun game, but it reminds me more of a mini-game or a mobile game in its simplicity.  There's not a lot of depth or complexity to running around a map throwing balls at your opponents.  True, there are different game modes, like a version of capture the flag, but I discovered I didn't care for most of these other game modes.  Playing dodgeball is where it's the most fun.  Unfortunately, I tired of even the primary game mode after about an hour.  I'm giving this a thumbs up though, cuz at the price I paid for it I must admit it's a well developed game with few flaws and it delivers on what it promises, a true dodgeball experience.  There just isn't enough there to keep me coming back.", "appid": "270450", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970507570", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533556800.0}
