{"text": "I don't leave many reviews, and when I do they are short and sweet, offering no information on the game and are usually comical. This is gonna be a long one so buckle up. TL;DR - 8.5/10  - As of right now, Temtem is in a pretty good spot considering it is still in EA. You don't have all the islands, all the Temtem, or all the features - but what you do have is a solid base from which this game will flourish. I don't want to talk about the art or music of the game, they are subjective but I personally love them. The controls are also solid whether played on either keyboard & mouse or controller - with no unnecessarily long loading times   gameplay simply flows, as going from area to area there are seamless transitions. Graphics settings their ain't much of but this game does offer native 21:9 support which is nice considering some bigger developers gloss over it - looking at you Fallout 4. I won't go into much detail on bugs either. - The 20 hours of content that is currently available is seen by some as only achieved by making you do a lot of back-tracking. You're right, there is back-tracking and quite a lot of it. But you can minimise this with smoke-bombs, stocking on medicines, and generally progressing throughout the game  - 76 Temtem currently in game out of the 161+ that is expected. That's not half bad. There is a good variety as you progress throughout the first island & gain access to new areas thus giving you a couple more Temtem to seek out in those locations. The one thing you'll notice is that your Temtem evolve after they've gained a certain amount of levels in your party, NOT at a specific level. Personally I like this change, as it makes you seek out the lowest possible level of your desired Temtem in order to evolve it quicker - or at least that's how I ended up playing. The one MAJOR downside at the moment is that there is no way in knowing what level your Temtem was when you caught it unless you remember. I currently have a Ganki at level 30 & get my hopes up every time the EXP bar fills. - Quite a bit more difficult that recent releases from that other franchise & if you've been bummed out with the most recent of those games due to difficulty, Temtem is a good option.  The big thing is \"stamina\" which is what your moves use. If you use too much then it damages your health and your Temtem because exhausted thus missing the next turn. I love the stamina system personally as it makes you actually plan ahead a bit and I find myself using buffs and items more than I did in other games.   - All fights are now 2v2 which also increases the difficulty a touch by offering synergies for some moves and a little bit more forward thinking than a 1v1 battle might require. NPCs can fight with 1 Temtem if they only have one, and untamed Temtem can appear as single or as a duo - you will always use 2 if you have 2+ Temtem in your squad. One thing that really REALLY grinds my gears is that there are soooooo many unskippable tamer fights. â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. It's like going through a gauntlet to get to the next clearing which will have you using your Temessence Vial, an array of healing items and maybe a smoke bomb to get back to the most recent Temporium. - Story & side-quests are alright. Actually, the story is good - so far - for this kind of game and exactly what you'd expect if you come from the other franchise, and the quests are so-so. You leave your house and set on a quest to become a great Temtem tamer then get your ass handed to you by your rival Max who's an â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. Sound familiar? The side-quests are just called quests and show up in the same category as the story quests but for the purpose of this review I'm splitting them. Reason being you can always tell which is the main one you've gotta do, but the side-quests can be fairly simple, or done just by playing and speaking to NPCs elsewhere. For example:  See that bold word? Expecting a huge list or a lot of complaints? Nah. The thing is, it's an EA game and if you're on the Discord server - or follow the official Temtem twitter account - you'll see how much work the developers have been doing recently. On launch night they were up throughout the entire night, then took a 5 hour break in the morning and resumed working on this game. They released 2 (or 3? I can't recall) updates within 24 hours of launch. They also released more hotfixes than I can count. They are dedicated and the communication is so reassuring that I can't get mad. I've had 2 freezes, 1 crash, and the bug where your Temtem would fill it's EXP bar then get a negative number and not level up - which has been fixed. They have been absolutely fantastic so far and hope they keep good levels of communication once the honeymoon phase has passed. I have - as of right now - 28.7 hours played meaning less than Â£1 an hour. Cinema tickets are Â£8~. Every hour I've played I have enjoyed thoroughly and cannot wait to pile more hours in, because I still haven't finished the content that's currently available. Game - 8.5/10 Crema - 9/10 Clan Belsoto - 0/10 Thank you for reading, thank you even more if your read the TL;DR then ventured down here, & apologies if anything mentioned is incorrect.", "appid": "745920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074843191", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1579953600.0}
