{"text": "The game is a supernatural detective thriller, where you play as a detective who was working at the Salem Police Department. The game takes place in the city of Salem, Salem is known as one of the most famous witch trials in the United States.  In the game you are a detective who tries to find out who his killer was, Ronan. The killer is known as: The Bell Killer. The police has no clues, no leads and no links between his victims. In the game you have the freedom to explore the modern-day town of Salem. Except trying to find out who his killer was, you can also solve the other side quests from another ghosts like you. They also wants to know something, like: how they died or did my boyfriend cheated with another woman before I died? When you first play you start with a cutscene that tells you the most important things you need to know at the beginning. After the cutscene you fell of a window and tells the most imptorant things of his past. After these cutscenes you can play the game, but the soul of your body got out after the incident. So you'll be trying to get in your body, but after getting shot by seven gunshots at your chest. Your body dies except the soul. He became a ghost, because he tries to resolve who his killer was. Normal people can't see you, except mediums. But there are also purposes of becoming a soul, you have abilities that you never had before like. Some of them are: Teleporting, manipulating- and to influence people. Souls can only die by Demons, whoa are trying to eat your soul and you die also by a red/black creepy hole.  My Impressions of the game: The game is really amazing and I had most of the times fun. The game looks in my opinion like The Wolf Among Us and L.A. Noire. In The Wolf Among Us you'll fall from a window too at the beginning, coincidence? The Pros and Cons. Pros - The game got good graphics - The game has besides a good main story, also good side missions - The game has trading cards - The game audio is well-made Cons - Sometimes there are too much demons in one room - The normal price is a little bit expensive", "appid": "233290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056604889", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466596800.0}
