{"text": "An action adventure game with heavy emphasis on adventure. Great cinematic experience. Yes, the game is very linear, filled you with a gameplay mixed of stealth, puzzle and some little bit of action then reward you with cinemation story progression. So while it might lack some immersive fun from the like of Hitman or Dishonoured, it has it's own charm. The storytelling, character writing and atmosphere go well together make this game feel like a good novel or TV series. The graphic is very detailed and help drive up the narrative+setting so well. As for Gameplay. It's big part of solving puzzle, another sizeable part some stealth/fighting but the fight is very simplistic save for some boss fights and enemies at the last chapter which can be tricky. Then it's about some lite resource management and crafting.  Talking about crafting, it has one of the weirdest crafting progression I've ever seen in a videogame with some early game upgrade use so much resources but seem really useless, while some late-game upgrade don't really have much uses when you have enough resource to upgrade them. Other than this gameplay is pretty balance and fine. They have enough resources to make player not get stuck. Item lying around can be taken as a hint for some puzzles or how to deal with enemies in the area. So this game is mostly for people who want to enjoy a good linear storytelling rather than experimentative gameplay...Not everyone's cup of tea but they serve nice jam scones ....so have my recommendation.  (Ending Spolier and my random rambling)", "appid": "752590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198837818261", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574251200.0}
