{"text": "This Review's formatting is Autistic, because I am, but to people raging it will make sense, for people who want to know why the 76% is prevelant and the 86 metascore is gashing fallout 4's good publicity, read on. META SCORE 86/100 STEAM RATING : Mostly Positive (76% at time of posting out of 21k reviews) \"GAME OF THE YEAR\" \"Board the Hype Train\" \"7 YEARS!!!!\" \"DAY 1 Gamebreaking bug,\" \"Graphics from 2011\" \"What the F*ck Bethesda?\" What did i tell people constantly since june?  Don't....... â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥............... hype, you're psychologically setting yourself up for a regression towards the experience that is realistically set by Bethesda, not some utopia based game. I am conflicted for having bought this, but everyone who is mad at them because of their \"expectations\" were not realized, shot themselves in the foot, and im guilty of it too. THERE IS A PSYCHOLOGICAL SCIENCE BEHIND THIS. But if you're going to have any decency and fairness in the review of this \"GAME OF THE YEAR\" Its downfall of publicity would be its inevitable hype surge, This is the problem with modern day marketing, i would of gladly taken a blindside SOFTLAUNCH, SOFTTTTT LAUNCHHHH! No warning, No commericals, No E3 spotlights. It would of completely leveied the people who are rating this down for hype reasons off of the table. Review copiers who broke their TOS agreement with Bethesda also are to blame for the spoiling of the story 3 days prior to launch. I hope this sets an example for Valve and anyone else who uses review copies as a means of getting publicity on day 1 launch. Humans cannot be trusted with the over bearing egocentric press hype that comes with being the first person to squawk a spoiler on a forum or sub par KDRAMA STARS CLONE crap. *Consensus* Half Life 3 will be doomed by its own fans more than the failure in production of its creators. Psychologically, hyping yourself is building up expecations to an unrealistic extent ruining the initial experience of the product you want. people need to learn self control, Psychologically if you hype for something, your expecations will be unrealistic and far from what you'll actually get. Causing a Regression of feelings about the games worth and throwing a fit because you were subject to your own hype. You then project your hate onto Bethesda with arguements like \"7 Years\" and \"Modern Day Graphics\", but when someone counters it with \"You've only played 2 hours.\", \"They had to combat the hype.\" \"The graphics actually relate to FO 1-2's video cutscenes style.\" and \"DLC is coming.\". You deny it, push yourself away and refuse to even awknowledge the game because you're so pissed that you didn't even get what you wanted. 60 dollars isn't a loss for an adult, you'll still have the game on your account. Im not excusing any incurrencies that Bethesda has implemented into the game, but i will not allow people to smash a game because of their own Psychological stupidity. Consider this as a punishment and a reminder not to hype a game", "appid": "377160", "steamid": "profiles/76561197991314163", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1447502400.0}
