{"text": "Hi to all you villagers. I have played many survival games over the years some good and some not so good but what makes a good survival game a success well it's smooth sharp crisp graphics and a sound that is out of this world with fantastic sound effects and a good FPM (A good Frame Rate) also how good the game is developed and each part of the game interacts with each other to make it a fantastic game worth playing and to enjoy it also needs to be a long playing game so to get value for money and to feel it is worth the money you spend. This game has been seen going for as little as Â£11.95 that's about $18 that is a fair price for this kind of game i am surprised it is not selling for around Â£25 to Â£30 as it is a new title just released and was released as early access but to my surprise it was released with very few bugs which most has been sorted out now by the developers the developers has worked so hard on this game with patches being released almost every day they are so dedicated to this game and to make sure it is the best survival game ever made i can honestly say from my point of view this is the best open sandbox survival game i have ever had the pleasure to play since i began playing PC games. For me i have an addiction to survival games i love them with a passion and i was looking forward for when this game was released as i knew it would be worth buying and playing and i am happy i bought it as it was money well spent. This game has all the elements in it you can grow crops and hunt for food and even set traps to catch food you also harvest almost everything from sticks and stones to oak trees everything in the wilderness was used in those days you can even fish for game and be a little naughty and steal other villagers crops and tools just don't get caught or seen doing it or it's off with his hands lol. also you can mine stone to get iron and dig for clay there is lots to do to make a successful village of your very own you can also hire villagers to work your village doing various crafts also take a wife and bare children so you have an successor to carry on after you as i said this game has everything in it even the 4 different seasons (Spring, summer, autum and winter) BEWARE there is animals in this game that will attack you and kill you such as wild boars and wolves and bears even bisen given half the chance even a fox will attack you if you attack it first so make sure you carry weapons with you when you travel anywhere. You do train up your workers to be better at various trades and look after them to a degree with food and weapons and tools and garments you need to interact with villagers first to get up your skills and reputation to hire them. There is much more to be added to this game as time goes on the developers are going to add a lot more to it i feel they intend to make this game the best survival game ever created lets hope they intend to release DLC to buy in the future at a low fair price.. WARNING!!! THIS GAME IS VERY ADDICTIVE ONCE PLAYED YOU NEVER STOP PLAYING IT YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED. All the items in this game are true to life as it was in medieval times which makes it much more nicer. The developers are nice and polite and very keen to listen to your comments and suggestions to improve this game much more which is rare to find these days a sign worth noting. So on a last point to my review i recommend this game to anyone who loves playing these type of games as you will be glad you bought it. GOOD LUCK and have fun playing it as much as i do.", "appid": "1129580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017082605", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1601640000.0}
