{"text": "Final Rating: 8/10. Worth the Price, Worth the Time. Cons & Pros: +Nice Graph, high gore, violently beautiful. +Great atmosphere, horror with black comic. +Balanced perks, well designed maps. +Nice music, really stimulating. +Even easy and friendly to new players, the Normal Difficulty is nerd-friendly, while high difficulties are full of challenge. =================================== -Still get stuck when launching, it sometimes take 20 mins to get into the main menu. #SOLVED#, some might say use -windowed or -dx10, but actually, if you played before and the game worked fine, it is due to the INVENTORY HOST SERVER, when this happens, you can unplug your network cable to solve this problem (worked for me immediately), or just disconnect to the Internet (haven't tried, but same theory), and then connect back online, but you'll fail to connect to the INVENTORY and SHOP (which is to be blamed). Hope the DEV FIX THIS PROBLEM, TIME IS TREASURE, I DON'T WANT TO SPEND HALF AN HOUR WAITING JUST TO PLAY ONE ROUND. -Some bugs including Screen Freeze, Input Disorder, and CTDs, but they're relatively uncommon. -Weird FPS drop, when I'm Rock'n'Roll, I get 144 FPS, when it's time for shopping, I get 80, strange. -Some designs seems lazy to me, like BOSSES, some are HUGE-SIZE normal Zeds, frustrating and strange. ================================== Neutral Parts: ~Not easy to build a LAN server, I confront problems when doing so (Not sure if I did something wrong, so I put this in Neutral.) ~Too violent, sometimes you get uncomfortable. ~Weapon skin bundle in high price, I don't buy and I don't recommend or stop anyone from buying, just saying, the price seems not so reasonable for me.", "appid": "232090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100361360", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591963200.0}
