{"text": "I completed the game in 1 hour and 30 minutes and I loved it, here is why: + The game has 9 levels (tests) total, each one is vastly different from another. You have different monsters to kill in each one, in some you can drive a vehicle, in others you don't even have a weapon and you mostly have to parkour to complete it. + Another thing I like is that you don't have to reload your weapons, once you pick it up, you can press the shoot button and never let go, that makes the big areas with many mosters slightly easier than it should, but I don't mind. + The boss battles are very satisfying and difficult, especially the one in Test 6, that one was a doosie. + NO CHECKPOINTS, you will die a lot and some levels are pretty lengthy, having no checkpoints makes the game much more difficult that it normally would be. I like that, saving anywhere you want is not to my liking, especially in a game like this. Sometimes it could be very frustrating ofcourse, but you can always replay the level. + Tha graphics are nothing special, but I love the art style, punching a wall and seeing all the bits and pieces of it fly in random directions is very satisfying. ============ The game has many flaws aswell: - Jumping is weird and very floaty, you don't know where you are going to land and sometimes you can't move mid-air. - Walking feels a bit weird too and also floaty, in some instances you can walk over a one block wide gap, in others you can't. This is very apparent in Test 6. - There is no A.I. whatsoever, the monsters just run at you and if they get stuck behind a wall, they will stay there and you can shoot at them until they die. Sometimes they even fall from the world if there is a gap between you and them. ============= Final words: I really liked the game. I got it for 14 cents with a 97% discount and already got my money back by selling trading cards, the game is worth so much more than that and I recomment it to everyone, once you get used to the jumpind mechanics, you will like it. It took me 15 minutes to see the appeal of it.", "appid": "303390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098597933", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1419076800.0}
