{"text": "I got the game for FREE, but I will be objective. PROS: - Interesting gameplay and unique, fun mechanics - Very aesthetic art mixed with a bit of weird art (both art styles mesh together well with the final product) - Good music, ambient sounds, effects and soundtrack - Good voice acting (not the best, but really good) - Variation in that the game will go easy on you if you miss the goal by a bit - Short and sweet - Family friendly and okay for ALL audiences to enjoy - Good jokes and mediocre puns that can make you chuckle CONS: - Bugs (there are bugs, probably related to the game engine or certain actions. Also seeing \"R.I.P. jokingly being stated for one of the studios behind this games, means that the developers probably have no intention of fixing anything) - The game is kinda orientated toward children and family playing together too much - Really short - it took me exactly 6 hours and I don't rush games and try everything possible (trying to find easter eggs, hidden areas and never looking for Internet hints) - Price is a little bit much for the game's cons. 5 euros seem a bit high - get it on sale (even 40% OFF will do) The pros outweigh the cons and I actually really enjoyed the game and geniuinely wanted to FINISH it, no matter how long it was.", "appid": "269330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198101035178", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564315200.0}
