{"text": "On one hand I understand why the mixed reviews. There's some bugs, crashing issues, the story is awful. The business model regarding DLC is insulting, and the world is full of repetitive activities built to extend game length.......But the gameplay is ****ing amazing. When there's two or three dozen enemies all trying to kill you and you've mastered your abilities and gunplay, the combat becomes a dance. A bloody, gory dance and I love it. Especially for 15 bucks.  There is a massive variety of progression mechanics in Rage 2. You upgrade each ability multiple times, each weapon and equipment. There's 4 skill trees that wildly impact the game. You upgrade your vehicle, health, damage, and \"Overdrive\" ability that acts as a \"WITNESS ME\" moment from Mad Max. Your health recharges, weapons take on alternate firing modes and damage increases drastically for upgradeable durations.  I love different forms of progression, so mixing that with one of the best first person combat systems I've seen since DOOM 2016 makes the whole ride very much worth it for me.  There's a ton of content here if you like to do everything. I can understand why critics would give this a mediocre score as the gameplay is phenomenal but the meat of the game is skipped in order to finish it. I very much recommend this game on sale. If you're a completionist and enjoy good first person combat you'll love this game.", "appid": "548570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043768190", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597406400.0}
