{"text": "TL;DR A potentially great game ruined by developer's design choices. I'll start off the bat by saying it's not a bad game. It's a good game... But it could have been a great game! The game is basically a remake of the 1990s series of games called \"Lemmings\", where you were acting as a God-like figure controlling a tribe of Lemmings, helping them reach a porta at the end of each level. Zombie Night Terror takes that classic formula, and enhances it further with Zombies. And humor. TONS of humor. What's not to like?! The game starts really great - It's funny... it has tons of pop-culture references... it's fun... We're having fun, what's not to like, right?! The thing is, while at the start of the game you're using logic to \"solve\" the levels, and a sandbox-style approach which allows you to take several different routes to solve the same problem. Somwhere around mid-game (for me it starts with the subway level), the game sucks out all the fun, by becoming extremely linear, with a single solution needed to be performed in a perfect timing. Instead of being a game it becomes a chore. Instead of being fun it becomes an exercise in frustration. I eventually finished the game, but it took cheats + watching walkthroughs to solve some of the levels. And it just wasn't fun... I recently finished reading Sid Meier's memoir, and I think we can all agree Sid Meier is someone who knows a thing or two about game design. And one of the things he talks about is that the main purpose of the game is for the player to have fun. It doesn't matter what's the most historically accurate representation of a game mechanic - what's important is what game mechanic is going to be the most fun for the player. It doesn't matter what's the most clever/challenging level a game designer can think of, what's important is what level design the player is going to enjoy. Too bad the developers of Zombie Night Terror haven't read that... So the game gets 6/10 from me (down from 8/10 for the first half of the game).", "appid": "416680", "steamid": "profiles/76561198014150309", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601899200.0}
