{"text": "Finished the tutorial, honest comments first: this game is crude, slow camera movements, clunky combat, questionable game balancing... However, this game has great potential. I see every addicting aspect in this game waiting to shine, all it needs is a little polishing here and there. Most importantly, you see someone chasing their dreams, you play their game, and you feel their passion. From this little indie game it found something long lost in me: the determination to overcome a challenge. It reminds me of the old days when games are used to be as crude as this, and players have to adapt, have to make do with what they have to win the game. Some games are designed to be difficult, and provide subtle mechanisms that allow you to snatch a win. This game provides you the basic blocks. It throws you in an arena, and you either fight or die.  Bad weapon damage and targeting? Oh well, hire more soldiers and use yourself as bait. Healing potions for soldiers are too ineffective? Forget healing and spam the most basic troops. Overwhelmed by enemies and don't have speed to save all the targets? Forget about assigning soldiers to locations. The targets can take a beating, think priorities and strike fast with a flash mob. Honestly this game is a surprising little gem, I can't wait until this game is finished. Last but not least, I would be grateful if achievements could be fixed as well :P", "appid": "1240240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004725788", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1591790400.0}
