{"text": "Weapons feel way too heavy, people that call this game realistic have never ever even touched a sword in their life (I have been practicing HEMA for a few months now), stabbing people is kind of fun but it feels too clunky and buggy, sometimes when you are too close to an enemy you wont be able to stab or damage them at all. Enemies parrying system is just crap, they basically put their weapons in front of them and follow your sword with them, if your blade slightly touches their weapon but then successfully hits their body, your hit wont be valid. Enemies with the big shield are impossible to kill unless you use the slow motion, locomotion system is either too slow (when walking backwards) or too fast (When walking forward). Merely touching an enemy's weapon damages you even if they were not attacking you while you have to do REALLY wide movements to actually connect a hit, which are easily \"parried\" by enemies. Oh and I still havent started with the bugs and glitches yet! Let alone all the damn crashes I have experienced in 3 hours however this is early access and it is his first dat on steam, so I wont take them into account. Cant refund anymore oh well.  EDIT After a while this game got much better since when I made this review, you can actually adjust the weight of your weapons, and the modding community is very active, with dismemberment and many other features this game is surely worth it's cost", "appid": "629730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124048645", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1544529600.0}
