{"text": "THIS GAME IS AMAZING!  Imagine a Miyazaki movie in the style of a metroidvania adventure game where the combat is replaced by playing pinball. The tables are usually small and there is a goal such as collecting runes to open a gate or trying to get characters to complete a bit of the story. There is no health or lives, if you fall you lose a bit of your fruit collection which is easily gotten back, and the only way to fail a table is to stop trying. But the world is very open and if you get stuck you can travel somewhere else and come back later, which I appreciate. Once you clear a table you can usually use fruit to unlock a paddle and pass it without having to go through it again, as well as unlocking paddles to access secret areas.  There is a demo available which encompasses the first part of the game. I played for 5 minutes and new I had to play the full version and I absolutely loved this game and recommend it to everyone.", "appid": "334940", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992552621", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1555243200.0}
