{"text": "immediately after publishing pyre, my favorite dev group starts development on one of the most engaging rogue-lite games yet, one that retells greek mythology, not only by following and respecting the texts it originates from but also interprets them with reverence, and is accompanied by a progressive metal soundtrack? is this what you're telling me? Playing this game at the point of development it is currently in, is extremely reassuring to me. The current game is one full of the artistic integrity that we've come to expect from the folks at supergiant, and one that not only manages to surpass all of its preceding titles in terms of scale, quality and gameplay to varying degrees, but ultimately demonstrates just how much these people have learned in the 10 years the studio has been in office for, something i believed near impossible after pyre. That being said many of the elements in the game are evidently not final, examples of this would be the absurd, nearly inexplicably volatile dps numbers some of the upgrades and variables offer/general balance, elements of the gameplay loops that struggle to maintain relevance in the lategame. its obvious a good portion of what is available right now could be heavily transformed in the near future and I only hope that whichever direction the devs take will be as brilliant as the current build of the game is, because what i've played so far has been as actively engaging as my first time playing wrath of the lich king. In my opinion Hades' biggest accomplishment is actually 'how' it lives up to its predecessors, admitedly as a rogue-lite its as distant from the pure \"rogue-like\" spectrum as possible due to how the game is actually structured and the kind of authority you are given over how your seeds will play out, how you customise your character and so on. Apart from that the story isn't as important to this game as it was in transistor or pyre even with the industrial amount of text and dialogue available. Despite this however, the world, atmosphere and its use of the greek pantheon come together to create an extremely provocative setting that separates it from its contemporaries in a genre that often only has something to offer to those looking for a very specific brand of game.  Its this matrimony between rich content and simple yet constantly fun gameplay that will form a habit of, thinking of an original way to tackle a run, trying it out on a legitimate seed consistently, and leaving a 3+ hour session having fulfilled  far more that you had originally envisioned.  Can't recommend it enough.", "appid": "1145360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198219949688", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1577620800.0}
