{"text": "Close to the sun is set in an alternative reality where Nicola Teslas invention shaped the world. The game is set on Helios, Teslas gigantic ship, which is basically a haven for the greatest scientists of the time. You are Rose Archer a journalist and sister to a briliant scientist Ada Archer, who lives on Helios. One day she sends you a letter, inviting you there. Stepping aboard, you quickly discover not all is as it seems. Not a person in sight, lights flickering and on a door you see \"QUARANTINE\" written in blood. Or red paint, who knows. The design of the game is outstanding, easily one of the games best qualities. Every location is very detailed and simply looks gorgeous.  Character models though, donâ€™t look particularly good. Atmosphere is really well done, it did feel quite scary at times. Gameplay is basically a walking simulator, where you walk around and read some notes and newspapers (interesting notes though), with a few chase sequences here and there. There are some puzzles, if you can even call it that. Its all quite primitive, no challenge there whatsoever. Story is quite good and thanks to the really good voice acting it makes it even better The game is very short, it took me around 4 and half hours. Performance is solid altough in the mentioned chase sequences I do get some frame drops. Iâ€™d say get this on sale, 20 dollars seems a bit much. I really donâ€™t think the game is as bad as people make it out to be, I really liked it actually.", "appid": "968870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098066392", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605441600.0}
