{"text": "So, after 4 years, I've decided to buy it. Put away buying it on release cause I lost faith in CoD for good, ever since Infinite Warfare (or advanced, or whatever warfare was before this one). As a die hard zombies fan, decided to pay tribute and buy the full zombies pack (Deluxe Chronicles) So the campaign is overly futuristic, fun to play, but is extremely hard to follow, so it basically requires no iq to complete or comprehend the story, cause there is none.  The multiplayer is legit trash, as a R6 Siege eSports player, I can tell you, that CoD multiplayer is a casual burning trash bin full of kids running around nadespamming and abusing meta guns. Got nothing wrong against meta, but in BO3 it is over the top. Take 2 guns. Vesper and the Haymaker. The former is a pocket minigun with a ridiculous fire rate. The latter is a MW2 AA-12 with higher range and a bigger magazine. OP? Decide for yourself Finally, Zombies. The main reason I even purchased this game in the first place. Gotta give Treyarch the credit, they remastered the gamemode properly up to standard. Even when activision tried to shove in a pay-to-win feature (the gobblegums), treyarch managed to make the game playable even for those, that don't want to waste money on a single zombies game. The maps are brilliantly retextured and reworked. Old glitches got fixed, no new ones were seen. The ability to customize and add attachments to guns in zombies (wall-buys and box weapons, though not all of them) shocked me in a good way. Conclusion:  Campaign:meh  Multiplayer:meh, too twitchy  Zombies:11/10 Recommending only to zombies fans atm", "appid": "311210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198185090361", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561723200.0}
