{"text": "The audio, visuals, controls and sheer scale of this game are second to none when compared to similar open-world games such as Saints Row, Just Cause or Ghost Recon: Wildlands. The singleplayer story is one of my favourites in modern gaming, with every character being entirely unique and bringin something to the game. The world itself is brilliant, with every NPC and interaction feeling unique. The multiplayer is fun, especially with friends. It is let down, however, by the pretty much NEEDED purchase of Shark Card microtransactions in order to experience any of the new updates. I did prefer it at release, when everything was attinable with work and you could look at a player's clothing, car or apartment and know instantly how much effort they'd put into the game. Now, however, anybody can buy anything they want if they are willing to spend real money on Shark Cards. Singplayer - 9/10, my only letdown being the presence of bugs which have been in the game since release. Multiplayer - 6/10. As much as I love the world and depth of the multiplayer, I cannot look past the P2W aspects. I would definitley reccomend this game if youre going to play wiht friends or only play single player/play wiht mods in single player. If you are getting it to play online on your own though, I would reccomend getting something else, unless you're wiling to grind for hundreds of hours or spend a large amount of money on Shark Cards.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070772797", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1507723200.0}
