{"text": "CS:GO (Counter - Strike : Global Offensive) was a very nice and cool game which I really liked to play alone and with friends. The community was never the best in the lower ranks but with the time it's even getting more worst. Because when you are playing in lower ranks you will meet many smurfers, hackers and troller ... Sometimes alone, sometimes as a whole team. But that's not all you also have teams which can't play as a team in lower ranks but in my opinion you need to live with it because you need to lern it how you play together as a team.  When you get higher you will see the diffrences. You have less hacker, toxic player, cheater, troller and so on. Here you also find players who know how they can play as a team (mostly). But it is not gettinger easier, because you need to lern the diffrent calls of the maps and the spray-controll of the weapons.  You also have the trustfactor which \"ranks\" your profile. That means if your profile is very unlegit because you get a ban on a steam game or getting much reports the trustfactorsystem says \"hey your trustfactor is bad! now you play also with hackers, troller and so on\". But one of the sad things is that the Trustfactor isn't working very well in my opinion... My trustfactor is low and I don't mean that it is slightly lower than the normal trustfactor. No ... My trustfactor is low as the middle point of the earth. So what I want to say is that my trustfactor is very low without any reason. My profile has at the time (24. January 2019) 2266 ingame hours, is level 62, the account value is between 163â‚¬ and 490â‚¬, is 6,8 years old and has 32 games on it. I can't understand why my trustfactor is so low because I'm a very serious player and I would never troll the team or would even hack. So always count that your trustfactor can be getting low everytime even if you are a serious player. Also in my opinion has CS:GO the best years behind because it's a game which need maps to survive and I can't understand why Valve take maps out without no really reason. If you want to play the game I recommend that you should buy it because when you buy it the chance is lower to play against hacker, troller and so on. Hope my review was helpful :D", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060385465", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1518696000.0}
