{"text": "BeatSaber is a rythm-music-kindof-slicing-game. You slice cubes in certain directions to a specific song. Basically Osu in VR with swords. Pro: - Costum tracks thanks for Mod support - Really great and doable starter songs - Multi- and Singleplayer - The option to only play with one controller / sword - A nice, effect fresh atmosphere - One hell of a workout Contra's: -  - Some modded maps do not line up with the beat | Not the games fault! - The tutorial doesn't mention how the scoring system works exactly - You really need to spend some time to get into it -  To the Scoring system: It's not like in Osu, where hitting the object perfect to the beat counts, but the way you slice it and how you do it. So technically, you don't have to care about the beat, but your movement. There is a video on the official BeatSaber Twitter explaining the scoring system. I think it should be included into the tutorial. I only came by it because someone told me about it. It's quite frustrating. The game is really fun. It's also one hell of a workout, but you just wanna keep playing.  The scoring system is frustrating, but there came a time when I hit that S-Score and reached the Top 10 and I just stopped looking at my score. You just...play.", "appid": "620980", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069208364", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "68", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1528286400.0}
