{"text": "First off, I apologize if this review feels like it's hastily written. I have intended to write a review for this game for a long time and stop more people from wasting their money on this and I just wouldn't have done it if I wanted to take everything into consideration. Honestly, there isn't much of a story here. This game has a wacky small story that can be finished in less than two days of playing and this story doesn't make sense for the most part, either. A lot of \"magic\" happens during it and characters do many things outside of the character they set up in the first encounters. There are 3 characters and each one of them is so â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ up in some way that it's hard to communicate with any of them. Most of the time you're just driving around or caught up with ridiculously easy gunfights... The map is big, sure, but it doesn't feel like you're having fun exploring you're just grinding to drive 13 kilometers to get the stupid missions done. It's just such a waste of San Andreas in the GTA series. The game offers zero RPG elements. You just complete boring missions and get paid so you can buy property that occasionally give you more boring tasks... All in all I can't think of much. It's really boring. Most of my single player experience was about doing boring tasks for the side missions. The side missions are actually longer than the main missions. Is also boring! You just grind to get enough money so you can buy a facility, office, bunker, whatever so you can trigger more slightly better rewarding boring missions. I really didn't feel much fun playing this game. The minigames known as \"jobs\" just feel like you're playing in an amusement park. Gmod would have probably done them better. I had some fun playing these small jobs at first, but after a couple of times they also become boring. Plus, doing them gives little reward so you can't buy â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ if you want to just keep playing those. You better grind so you can actually afford a good car. As far as PvP gameplay is concerned, 99% of the fights are unbalanced. The power distance between the hardcore players and the new ones is just ridiculous. One player can have an arsenal of super soldier stuff at his disposal, and another dude doesn't even have 60% of that dude's max health because his rank is low! The playerbase is also one of the most toxic ones I have ever seen. Well you might think that a game of this size from such a well-known company can offer a solid multiplayer experience. WRONG! Me and almost all of my friends in the western Asia and eastern Europe region have experienced a great deal of basic connection issues... long long long loading screens (maybe even for 15 minutes!) just to join a game session that is super unstable and randomly just disconnects. This sucks more when you have got to have 4 players on board for most missions and when someone is forcefully disconnected, the mission is lost for everyone else. I don't have any connection issues with any other games and the single player loading screens load just fine (I don't have any problem with loading screens in any other game either). The multiplayer, on the other hand, is another story. Needless to mention the many stupid bugs you will experience with the Rockstar Launcher that just HAS to be run before the game can launch... Sometimes it's just unplayable. Imagine having one hour to play games and spending maybe 55 minutes staring at loading screens just to disconnect and sit at another loading screen again and again and again. Also, the servers are hacker infested and in this game they don't just piss you off by using cheats like God mode to troll you, no that would be too kind. They can set your character on fire, drop cars on you, spawn a million angry bots to kick your ass, place unwanted props and characters in your properties forever and many more... They can even buff your character or transfer a huge sum of money to your account so that the game detects YOU as a hacker and gets you suspended or banned... The graphics are the only good thing I can find about this game, even though they're not the best now. Audiowise the game is ok. There are a handful of good songs on the game radio and the rest is just trash. Not the stuff I would like to get used to when driving around for about 70% of my gameplay time... The physics are also not bad, but certainly a downgrade from GTA IV. The cars feel like toy cars that you can even tilt around! All in all, this game had nothing to offer more than the previous games in the series and for the most part it was a downgrade. It wasn't fun like GTA I and II. It didn't have the solid story and adventure of GTA III, Vice City, and San Andreas. It failed on continuing the strategic elements of San Andreas. It didn't have the wonderful physics of GTA IV. The multiplayer experience was just awful and definitely not worth it. The only good part about it was the graphics which is not a main factor of a good game. This game is just overrated. I would give it a 3/10 for a modern game. This title in the series just let me down hugely.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198438224666", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581768000.0}
