{"text": "I really like VNs and I also like Asian art-style, culture, etc. (normally). But this game does so many things wrong, in my opinion, that I can't play it (and won't pay for it - although I got it really cheap; it's just not worth the time I would have to spend). - And I can't recommend it at all. Here are the reasons: Judging from the pictures and the trailer it looked really interesting and the overall story-hints in the game description weren't bad, either, but the shock came after starting a new game. The first unpleasant thing I had to notice was the absence of any music or sound (I had no voiceovers, too, because I turned them off in the options - since I don't understand the language). Despite a very nice and well performed main-menu music, there wasn't any little  noise to hear after starting the game - just silence (and it continued until the protagonists reached the next town - then there was some (generic) music again, but only to cease completely again, after leaving the first location). And then the next shock: All the text in the game is not formatted to fit in the window where it is shown - that means, that every word that would be longer than this window (at the right side) is just cut in half / divided in the parts of the upper and the next lower line, independent of its normal syllable division or its length - even a word containing of 2-3 letters, like e.g.\"the\" is cut down to \"t- he\" or \"th- e\" - in my opinion that's just ridiculous ! And for a game - a VN - that lives almost completely from reading all the time that's just a really big annoyance ! - Then the next strange thing (to say the least) - that isn't of the same importance and that also depends on personal taste, but that was an absolutely NoGo for me - is the look of all of the main characters: They all look like girls / women, despite the fact that they address each other like boys / men (and I don't mean the look ot their bodies - they all have the same, or a very similar physique and you couldn't tell if they are man / woman because of the many clothes they are wearing - No, I mean the look of their faces; they all look like (more or less) beautiful girls / women, with purely feminine facial characteristics !) And then, lastly the choices - normally a very important part of any VN: Not only, that there weren't any until the main characters reached the next town (although they had a little fight and many quarrels and conversation in between), but they also only consisted (mainly) of the choice where to go next, without any hints or reasons given why it would be better to do one thing or another or where would be the difference at all. Just: \"Go East\" / \"Go West\" / \"Leave the town\" ... and then after choosing an option there appeared another picture, but the music died again and there only where played some little short sounds (and only once) when a special line of text appeared - no environmental sounds / music - nothing ! - That was the time I really gave in and decided to write this review (instead of playing the game). I'll leave it to you and your own judgment if you also would like to buy it (or really play it), but if I would have known these things beforehand, I certainly wouldn't have bought it. ;-)", "appid": "787370", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992644299", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583496000.0}
