{"text": "Undyne in the Genocide run is plain not fun. Genocide run is the most imbalanced non-fun part of the game yet everyone talks about it. Shouldn't have been included due to the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ DDR non-fun gameplay mechanics of Undyne. Undyne in general was not an enjoyable character both from a gameplay and story standpoint. Removing her completely from the game and replacing her with Toby the Dog would've improved the game. Undyne was an over-the-top unrelatable tsundere jerk treated like she's some great friend and misunderstood character when she's neither. Game directly insults the player for playing the content they bought. Being self-referential doesn't take away from the fact I don't want to be insulted for fully using the content I purchased, especially given that the pricetag can't be justified without multiple play-throughs. Game's sense of ethics is so black-and-white against any form of killing it ruins the gameplay experience because everyone gets bothered by self-defense or killing legitimately horrible monsters. Sans is treated as an ultra powerful highly important character, yet is never explained within the game. Given that after years of theorizing nobody has figured out what his deal is, that's not a clever mystery -it's just poorly explained empowerment of a lazy character. Strikes me as a self-insert on the part of the game's creator. Also does nothing of interest unless you go out of your way to suffer through the game's â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ hateful judgement of the player for *gasp* playing a route in the game that doesn't align with the game's ideology. Not to mention that route is again incredibly poorly balanced without any proper difficulty buildup and a prior boss battle with Undyne that's built around â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ DDR memorization rather than actual skill.", "appid": "391540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065405576", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created"