{"text": "Mordhau was lot of fun during the first month after release, but beyond that, the lethargy of content development and moribund player base has become excruciatingly apparent. The existing build suffers from an abundance of balancing problems with both maps and equipment, and a deficit of stable servers and playable maps. Yes, there are still lots of server issues, even after recent improvements, and most remain capped at 48 instead of the official 64 player limit. Joining one of the few 64 slot servers while they contain more than 54 people will introduce instabilities in performance and constant packet loss. The game lacks any kind of modding tools, and the developers have made it clear that releasing such tools is a low priority for them. The existing 8 maps (4 large for Frontlines and 4 very small for Deathmatch) will get very old very fast for most folks. I'm not counting Crossroads because that map is little more than horses and spawnkilling; having no objectives also means that the only way to end a match on Crossroads is to fully drain your opponents tickets, which takes a long time, being that there is only a single zone to capture. TL,DR I cannot recommend this game in good conscience unless you are willing to accept its numerous problems with balancing, server performance, and lack of modding tools, as well as the likelihood that the game may not be updated beyond its current state. Even then, you may want to look/wait for a sale.", "appid": "629760", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998364683", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564660800.0}
