{"text": "While I enjoy what story I've seen, and applaud the variety of unique character options.  I cannot recommend this game because it is a buggy mess still even this many years after release. As a game its pretty decent when it works.  It may not be perfectly balanced (or even nearly so) but that doesn't mean it isn't fun.  And one can quibble over the class changes for the original. The real problem are the bugs that continue to go unresolved.  The worst issue is a \"saving bug\" where something happened and now the game will not save my progress.  One time, I logged in and out, clicked the \"Go online\" button on and off multiple times, entered \"multiplayer mode\" backed out and managed to get it to save, but the next time I played, back to not saving.  This is in addition to sporatic game start issues.  Say 25% of the time one tries to start the game, the graphics do not load properly and you have to close the game and re-open it.  Then there are a signifucant number of crashes to desktop to deal with.  Sometimes 10 second pauses to switch and inventory item (usually a weapon is the worst).  It's a buggy mess. There are the usual terrain snags but overall, as a game (if it were mostly free of bugs), I would recommend it, but given so many serious issues 4 years after release, this game cannot be recommended.", "appid": "400170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198119915053", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540209600.0}
