{"text": "I refunded this garbage. If you wanna know more, read below. I installed the game, which is already massive for what it does: almost 40GB. That's insane. Still, I wasn't gonna let game size deter me, so I entered the game with hopes and aspirations of a grand, amazing game reminiscent of the old, badass days of Agent 47 when I was a teenager. Boy was I disappointed. First and foremost, you can't even get through the first trial mission without there being bugs present. In 1 playthrough, I ran into two: 1) When pouring an item, like to poison something, the bottle was held upside down, as if he was pouring it out of the bottom. Small, but incredibly piss poor bug that shouldn't exist in a game allegedly this good. 2) When the target drank the poisoned tea, she got sick, and then started just randomly walking in one direction. She walked across the table/chairs, through the wall, out into the field, and then teleported to the edge of the map, where she T posted. I ran over to her and shot her in the head. No reaction. She was invulnerable. Game breaking bug. That was just on one playthrough. I also had her do summersaults when I tried to drown her in the toilet. I had one of the guards' ragdolls freak the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ out and crash my game. I had 2 randoms CTDs happen for no apparent reason, in different places. This all happened in less then 1 hour of gameplay. Unacceptable, even at a summer sale discount. I don't know why this game has this massive amount of positive reviews, but I'm definitely not impressed. In fact, I'm downright appalled. Refunded the game. Never buying another Hitman game. They've turned into complete garbage.", "appid": "863550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033807841", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562241600.0}
