{"text": "I'll keep this short.   Refund requested for the $1 I spent.   Avoid if you find futzing with game settings and Windows settings frustrating. If you are a fan of Sonic games and are willing to deal with Havok engine messing up your system settings, go for it. The game is pretty, plays smoothly and appears to provide the Sonic experience.     The above are Pros: Cons:  - No controller rebinding button layout configuration. - Configuration tool failed on first attempt and game refused to launch until the 'configuration tool' was setup and saved.  No instructions on how to find the \"configuration tool\" so some computer savvyness required... like knowing how to look in your Steam Install directory for any given game. - Unacceptable settings and configuration settings for a modern game. - Had to reboot my machine 2 times per play session to get my Windows 10 settings back to normal and to get the Steam client to even function again.", "appid": "71340", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996084333", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "11", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593345600.0}
