{"text": "Ah.. Smite. I have a few thousand off of steam. Got to masters. Had grandmasters towards the end of the season 2. Stayed in masters throughout up until quite recently. Smite was a game I learned how to play mobas. It was fun. Easy to learn. Hard to master. Unlike league where its hard from the beginning. I love how you can buy all champs for $30. I dislike how inconsistant a lot of the skins are. Towards design and etc. The game honestly does get boring in the end. Your ranked teams are either godlike or absolutely terrible, even in the extremely higher elo's. People make jus.. Dumb noob mistakes. I mean, worse then league of legends even. And there is a certain point in the game where you cannot carry no matter how good you might be. The champs are honestly TOO balanced, even some of the newer ones. Juking skill shots is beyond easy. It's actually depressing. I recommend this game to learn. Not to stick with. I play LoL as of now. Still climbing the ranks and I will gladly admit that this game is the sole reason as to why I even got nearly as good as what I would of been at LoL if I didnt play this game. Not saying I am amazing at LoL. This game is terrible as the long run. The game does need some broken retarded gods that need to be focused and shut down. And He Bo does not count. The assassins need to be able to one shot and leave and still participate in a team fight. The tanks need to be tanky enough to peel to prevent that from happening. The mages are in a great position, and hastened fatalis was and is still necessary and why did they take it out of the game is beyond me. Kiting on an ADC is nearly pointless as of now unless you have a reliable CC and/or reliable escaped. Hou Yi for example. I learned this from several mobas. Not jus LoL. Without a carry being able to carry will ruin a game. The game is incredible for the difficult learning curve of mobas. But thats about it.", "appid": "386360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067633164", "voted_up":