{"text": "Long time player here, I really liked state of DB one year before (with exception of huge lack of updates, if only I know what will happen back then), but then some very questionable decisions from SD( Splash Damage, developers) happened. I thought that I will be better so I didn't write review after crafting update, but no, instead it became much worse. So, lets see what happened in a past year, shall we? It all started with change to crafting system. Before it was chain of crafts which allowed you to craft from lower rarity to highter, which allowed you to keep some good cards on the way to highter rarity. After it was replaced by fragments plus if you wanted to increase your chances for desirable from 1/9 to 1/3 you could buy â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ of materials for RL cash only. What a nice addition. Then happened really empty Christmas event, which can be described as just play for long time and get your trinkets. Then there was Turtle update with exclusive skins. The main difference from Aimee update was that instead of paying 100 000 credits for 100% chance of getting event skin, now 100 000 credits would reward you ONLY with 10%! What a generous change, SD! Thanks for thinking about players. And it may not even drop with that percentage, it took way too long time for me to get a drop with 15%. Next one, ranked. Don't go there. DON'T DO IT. It is one of the most unbalanced rankeds ever. It was better BEFORE they allowed FULL premade teams vs everyone else. Unranked vs hightest rank is pretty common situation too. But the most thing that got me pissed it ranked were... spawncamping Fraggers that can wipe out from half to full of your team running from spawn. You'll see them in EVERY game on highter ranks. But instead of nerfing Fraggers( or giving some spawn protection from explosives) lets nerf Thunder for 4 or 5 patches in a row, cause he is so  OP. And speaking of balancing things. If SD decides to buff or fix some perks on cards, it's pretty common for them to instead of buffing perk, nerfing cards without that perk. So cards with perk would look like they were without perk before update pretty much making cards without that new shiny perk perk obsolete. It now happened to Aura with potent packs, before same thing happened to Rhino with nitro. And now for the thing that will make me uninstall this game- they are removing Execution gamemode. Why? Why can't they just leave it as it is. Not everyone likes to rush to EV, grabbing cores, etc, there were something nice in preventing enemy strategies, thinking of your mistakes being ghost while helping with chat and doing ace while whole team is dead and rooting for you. As you may guess it was my favourite gamemode with Gallery being a masterpiece map. And don't tell me that only 5% of playerbase is playing it, I could always find servers to join. Speaking of server browser. Devs are gonna add casual matchmaking so that you can't join any server that you want. What is this WOT? Though as far as I heard there will be some ghetto servers for those who prefer server browser but I may be wrong. Plus current event (Final Assault update) which lets you get event skin with huge chance of 2%! from case for 1000 credits. Would be nice to have those skins with 100% chance for 100 000 credits like they were in Aimee update, but we are dealing with SD here, 100% cases are for RL cash only. So, yeah, the chain of bad and questionable decisions with removing Execution( game will have only one gamemode after removing, objective and stopwatch are same) on top have made me to really dislike this game plus it's just don't fun to play for me anymore. PS: recently they added daily rewards for finishing matches, and before writing this review I got 3 matches finished and no reward so thx, bye.", "appid": "333930", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993571582", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "185", "votes_funny": "15", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1502539200.0}
