{"text": "My recommendation is based on my ideal type of video game. Pros:  - Looks gorgeous - BD-1 is the cutest little droid - Interesting Story & Lore Secrets - Combat is smooth and good if you know what you are doing. - Good voice acting Cons: - The boss fights are ridiculously hard. I played on Jedi Knight difficulty which is essentially 'Normal.' and I quote it says 'Forgiving Combat' It took me easily 7/8 tries to defeat some of these enemies. Takes me roughly an hour per boss (end game bosses.) IMHBHO that is not forgiving. If you make a single mistake and any of these fights, you're â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥.  - Spawn Points, you can easily trek miles away, fighting enemies left, right and centre, only to be killed by a big Goat Slug and spawn all the way back a the start to face them all again. -  As of 23/11/19 the game still has lag issues due to poor optimisation, even on the PS4.  - Stressful. This game is beyond stressful, I find myself being stressed throughout these missions. Simply because the amount of pressure on you to not â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ it all up is intense.  - Boring at times. There are times where the game runs out of ideas and goes 'I know! lets put he in a room and make him battle waves of enemies one after the other. *Yawn*  - Unnecessary. Some bosses it adds into the game make no sense. For example: a big bat. Pointless, only in the game for funsies or in my case Stressies.  - It is a 9 hour campaign. Took me 30 hours to complete, despite me not really going out of my way to find any chests or loot. - Trilla is a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥.", "appid": "1172380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067254228", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574164800.0}
