{"text": "Like everyone else I had high hopes for this game. Unfortunately GreedFall was huge let down for me. I'm not gonna lie, first 5+ hours were actually fun, I had Dragon Age 2 and other older rpg feels.  But.  Soon after game become a chore and I dont remember when i was so drained out playing a game. If that game came out in early 2000 it would be a hit. For today standards it just doesn't deliver. (I know that this game was made by a small studio of 20-30+ people but my problems were not with graphic or flashy gameplay and action) I cannot recommend GreedFall at almost triple A price. Wait for 50% sale. Cons: - companions. I couldn't connect with anyone, all were uninterested without any ambition or goal and they didn't bring anything to the story. Even after loyalty missions I couldn't feel any connection. Also there were no memorable side characters. - battle system. Lazy and easy. Companion AI is dumb as f**k.  As a mage i was just smashing left mouse click, dodge is broken because it requires no mana or stamina, not once did I block or used any other skill beside Stasis and maybe one or twice that aoe stasis. I have play on hard mode. - character progression. Talents are useless. I have never touched crafting and alchemy (npcs can do that in towns) Lockpicking? From almost all chests you get 1-5 gold, some ingredients and 1-3 ammo, i think there is a chest or two where you find good gear. vigor? Useless. Only charisma and and maybe intuition are worth. Attributes are plain minimum like +100 hp, mana, +10% dmg etc. Skills. Again bare minimum.  - Gear. I have been using Vasco's chest armour from beginning to the end. Every time i got new wep i couldn't feel any difference. - environment. Not gonna lie it looks beautiful. BUT. Towns are too big and that wouldn't be a problem if there were things to explore. They just waste your time. Those 3 houses that you can enter are also huge and labyrinth like just to waste your time. People just stand around like from early ps/ps2 era. - quests. They have drained me the most with all that constant running from one part of map to another just to immediately run back. Some were interesting but that running around ruined (even with fast travel) especially quests where you have to wait for 24h. - conversation. Unlike Dragon age where you have multiple options to chose here you have Charisma answer, bribe or something like threaten/convince. - few types of monsters and copy paste bosses. - some minor bugs and fps drops Pros + Story is actually ok. + Refreshing setting. Not your typical fantasy with swords and magic.  + Environment is beautiful + Game makes you want to play older rpg classics + Not an open world.  Spider studio is on the right way. I hope they will listen to feedback and that they will keep improving. 5.5/10", "appid": "606880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198314163573", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572436800.0}
