{"text": "So finally it has come to this. After nearly 1000hrs I am finally done with this s**t game. For the clueless: This game has pretty much not improved since its early access status. At one time it was so bad, that there was a \"fix pubg\" campaign. This campaign has since vanished for the dumbest â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ reason I have ever heard from a game studio. Fixing the errors was just too hard. Instead we get more uninspired cosmetics with either a stupendously low chance of getting them from the LOOT BOXES (yeah you heard me), or incredibly irrational prices in the shop. The graphics are just not next gen, the textures especially seem really low quality. Some might say I just did not crank the graphics high enough, which is an entirely valid assumption, given the fact that i can barely play it on high settings with my GTX 1080. Which brings me to my next point: The developers are totally clueless and this is one of the worst optimized games I have ever played. I can play CoD Modern Warfare (the new one) on highest graphics and it doesnt even use as much of my graphics card, while still looking magnitudes better than this brick of a game What finally pushed me over the edge was the recent decision of replacing my favourite map Vikendi with a 2kmx2km map, on which still 64 players drop. This has managed to take most of the skill out of the game for me, because you start off in a sandwich situation, looting a double barrel shotgun, while getting blasted with automatic rifles from 4 different directions. If youre not lucky enough to loot the right weapon for your situation nearly instantly, thats it for that round. Dying to terrible timing is now 10 times more likely. That was the final straw. Please dont feed this â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ game studio any more money. They burned through most of the money they had (which was truly a lot) in no time, all while making a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ mobile game and not fixing the one that made them their money in the first 