{"text": "Though it looks cute, there is no explanation of controls. Heck there's no explanation of anything. There's very little feedback on whether you've hit an enemy or not, and enemies start off very hard, needing 4+ hits to kill. The 'hit' animation is 'tears' on the enemy character, no 'physical' feedback i.e. the character getting jostled, and no audio feedback,  The only setting is for sound or not, which at the moment is a drumbeat which doesn't change very much.  To control your character, you can use the arrow keys or A/D and spacebar, but the only way I found to attack is with the mouse button.  The first couple levels should have been quick things to draw you into the game, but instead you sit there clicking and jumping to kill the first couple enemies wondering why your character slides around so much as if he's on ice.  As the game currently stands, I'd skip it. Though if some improvements come to the game, perhaps it'd be worth playing, as I liked the concept, but not the execution.", "appid": "801510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985759517", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1519387200.0}
