{"text": "It took me a bit to start this review... I loved the previous 2 games, but this one gave me mixed feelings. It's a turn based strategy game, with RPG elements, where your choices make a difference and influence future events. The visuals are lovely, as is the music, and the whole Viking theme on a world of magic and mistery. The graphics continued to improve on this last sequel, with more cut scenes, more characters, more items (especially if you load a previous save from Banner Saga 2, continuing the previous adventure), a whole different set of scenarios, and the closure to an ever wonderful and exciting story. According to the choices you make on this game (and the previous ones), you will also be rewarded with different endings. So why the mixed feelings? Banner Saga 3 was to me a bug riddled experience. Other users have had the same problems - the game crashed frequently, either stopping on an \"infinite loading\" screen, or sometimes exiting from full screen to windowed and... crashing: Banner Saga 3 \"not responding\". So I would have to close the game's process and restart it from the last autosave. Also worth mentioning, I had no issues on Banner Saga 1 or 2. Game support suggested reinstalling, checking game file's integrity, some people said steam online sync should be disabled, etc. I was unable to find a solution, so ideas aside - it's bugged. To make it worse, this was released in 2018, and is still not fixed, so it seems Stoic just dropped the ball on this one and proceeded to other projects. This was annoying enough, and once I finished it, I just put it aside, with no intention to further explore the game, other choices and endings. Recommended for those who want to see this story reaching an ending. As a standalone game, not recommended - not until it's fixed.", "appid": "485460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056575983", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580990400.0}
