{"text": "o7 Commanders and fellow viewers of this review, So, what did we get after a month of waiting? The list below are  , everything after that is my   on them.  The test is Public, this is generally good, although I feel FDev forgot LEP buyers still exist. Usually I'd say a week 2 months before the update is weird and small, not this time though.  First of all, for me personally \"longstanding issues\" (like FDev calls them) never were network/crash bugs, they were more about gameplay and QOL. But okay, let's digest; I won't be giving too many details, since it's all in the post available to everyone.  So, what's my opinion of this mess? Guess we'll have to wait and see...what I do see right now is that the update will be lackluster, so will the second one probably. There are many more bugs that are much more annoying; this stuff however? This stuff is only justified if the bugfix team consists of one person, and I don't think that's the case.  I guess the sole reason I'm not diving into a full-on detailed rant is because this is a review, and the review is generally the same, FDev as of right now couldn't care less about the game or the fans.  Elite Dangerous Community Update post was published on 22/10/19. This part of the review was updated on 22/11/19 to make the review slim.  Beta tests are back, but   FDev pushed Fleet Carriers to Q2 (April, May, June) of 2020, to give us patches that'll take \"3-4 months\", so basically 2-3 patches at max (keep in mind, these are small bugfixes). At the time of that post being published, there was no info on how much bugs and which specific bugs will be adressed (it only said \"longstanding issues\"), keep this in mind when reading new updates (e.g. 22/11/19 onwards).  Since this edit was cut  , I'll iterate once more... No understaff, no new expansion, not even fleet carriers justify how bad FDev cares about this game, much less about its fans. One year ago? Maybe two years, I'd wholeheartedly say that Elite Dangerous is   space game to play. Now? There are none, Elite degraded to the state of it's competitors, sucking money and not caring about their fans.  With the new patch (18/09/19), cosmetics are now available for purchase with ARX, yet to get something interesting you'll need to spend up to 14000 ARX, that's with 400 ARX per week limit.  Oh and normal purchases via real money are now removed, you can only buy packs of ARX to then purchase something.  Seriously why concern yourselves with fans, LEP buyers, other constant players, and balancing stuff, fixing bugs, introducing new content, which we've not seen since 2015 (Horizon DLC); when you can just make tutorial missions that don't even teach you how to use flight assist, make some yearly QOL improvements that seem like they took a day at maximum, and introduce scummy monetization.", "appid": "359320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049021687", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "98", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1568894400.0}
