{"text": "So, the game is not the worst thing I've ever played, but it's definitely not worth the trouble/cost. In the beginning, there seems to be some promise of better, deeper combat and gameplay, but by the time you get mid-way through the second area, you realize that the concept falls completely flat. The core mechanic is fighting through \"dungeons\"(?), killing a block of enemies and looting new equipment until you are strong enough to beat the area boss. That fighting is extremely repetitive. Monsters follow a script, and your job eventually just becomes learning the rotation to not die, until you get strong enough to kill them with one hit. This is boring. There's no real strategy or variation to speak of. Beyond that, the grind is insane, for no real reward. Once you reach a certain level, enemies simply stop providing experience; the reward does not diminish - it simply disappears. This is not the end of the world as many RPG games work this way. Why it's a problem here is that in order to battle with enemies that WILL provide XP, you must fight through 10, 20, 30+ 0 XP waves first. This is infuriating and makes the game take significantly longer for no reason whatsoever. I'm playing through the third area right now and trying to force myself through to the end for the achievements (i.e. I'm a glutton for punishment). All of the achievements are a reward for patience, no skill/investigation required for any of them. I would not recommend doing the same unless you REALLY want those achievements, too. After 8.5 hours, I've seen all there is to see in this game and then some, but I fear I have many, many, many more hours to go before I can get the 100% I'm working towards. Games should not be chores.", "appid": "315320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127957838", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581940800.0}
