{"text": "I couldn't stand an hour of playing, before I had to quit and uninstall. I played Audition avidly 8-9 years back, on the Nexon platform. Looking back at it, it really wasn't all that unique or exciting. I lost my account too, so I had to start anew again, which I was fine with. The flaws encountered playing, I was not.  Starting with character creation - the game does not let you decide your gender. You identify as a female during the sign-up process the game auto-locks your gender. Lame. There's about 3 servers when I last logged in, with the first one being the only one with 10+ channels. The game is pretty dead, so I was able to jump into channel 1 that had the most, and only players, active there.  On the map menu, everything you can do for your character - including tournaments, photos, and shopping - starts here. I never really touched on the FAM Office, Audition studio, Photo Studio or Couple garden. Even back then, because they were just simply extras that the game can live without. The options on the top are a bunch of lined cubes. I attest how the game options only allows you to adjust the BGM or volume. The developers were so focused on making this game as music-supported as possible that they completely ignored other important settings, such as screen resolution change, graphics quality, key bindings etc. I have one damaged arrow key, and frankly play games with the AWSD keys, so the latter being unavailable ruined majority of my play time. The Dancing Hall and Shopping place are the only 2 good features that Redbana made. The dance Hall is where you get to play either solo, or with other players in a variety of different modes. The game is constantly adding new songs to play too, so kudos for that. It's entire rooster list is still mediocre though, as majority of them are imitations or Remixes of the original song. In the game-play itself, expect the lowest graphic animu characters with stiff movements and buggy timing. I question the hit bar timing for the space key. At times there will be one or two players who dances off-sync with the other players, as though the system failed to catch them up to the current dance moves. Also, 80% of the player's dance moves aren't suited for the music, lol. It's all RNGed. You start the song with 4-6 keys to hit, which grows to a max. of 9 by the chorus followed by a Finishing move. Then it's repeated again as long as the song runs. The arrows you hit are also not meant to be in-sync with the music either - you only end up hurrying to click all 9 keys correctly and not focus on the music at all. In short, it's hard to identify Audition as a proper rhythm game. When you boil it down, it's really just 1) Arrow spam, then 2) Hit space for every 3 passes on the blue area in the bar. The Shopping mall is where you can pay with RL $$$ all the prettiest things you can find. I didn't buy anything  . Items for your character can be unlocked when you completed missions and lvl up too in the game. But why bother, when the graphics, settings and game-play are all made by a cheap, low-budget program? Redbana clearly didn't consider upping these features, and even MMD can run better animations than this. As mentioned earlier, nothing's really changed in the game besides the song list increasing. Looking back, I remember 15 yr-old me being irked about the same issues. The game's been abandoned, and was somewhat good for it's time. Now, I wouldn't recommend touching Audition, even to veterans.", "appid": "349720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079704709", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570449600.0}
