{"text": "Do you remember those \"Choose Your Own Adventure\" books? Well this game is nothing like those, in fact it is like the worst kind of incarnation of one of those that was terribly assaulted by a manga monster and now has to seek counselling to recover. You essentially have to guide your character through the game exploring the branching story line and discovering different endings. The game has a few moments that are quite funny interspersed with completely inexplicable segues and moments of existentialist angst.  The bizzare disjointed story combined with the amount of repitition in dialog and gameplay leads you to tire of the game rather easily, and makes it feel like One Mage Day Too Many instead. On the plus side the game is free, only around 100mb and not too long having taken me less than an hour to deplete all options. There is also a skip feature that lets you skip dialog that you have already read before. The game's achievements are rather easy to obtain as well, making it ideal for achievements hunters. In conclusion : If you are looking for an interesting manga based game, look elsewhere. If you are an achievement hunter looking for an easy 100% then this is for you.", "appid": "365070", "steamid": "profiles/76561197989930340", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1431518400.0}
