{"text": "I originally played Okami on the Wii. In my memories it was a pretty great game with gorgeous graphics, fun gameplay, a neat story and cool characters. I wish I had left it to stay in my memories because only one of those is true. The graphics are still amazing. Everything else though is a severe disappointment. First of all there's way too much dialogue throughout the entire game. Everyone talks way too slowly and way too long about absolutely everything. Everywhere you go you have to stop and listen to someone, then listen to Issun stop and explain what was just discussed, then when you get to the place listen to a repeat of what was talked about and how you do it again.  This also ties in with the constant forced tutorials about everything, and how the pace of the game is just awful. You're learning new things throughout the game which is fine, but every time you reach a point where you might need to use one of your abilities on the main quest Issun will stop and remind you just what you need to do to get past. Even if you've had this ability for hours by that point. The pacing is even worse when it comes to the way the story goes. The game starts with a huge main big threat, and you fight that big huge threat after a big event happens several hours in. Then you beat it... and the game is only 1/3 over, you've got 20 more hours to keep playing even though you just killed the final boss didn't you? Nope, you didn't. It also treats women terribly. Every single female character relevant to the story is either treated as eye candy or a damsel in distress or a manipulative villain, sometimes all three. It's just a huge shame. I guess the game was always like this, but I don't remember it being so. If anyone else is in my similar position of having played it already years ago, keep that memory close and don't taint it by returning to try again.", "appid": "587620", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972662016", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "11", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559131200.0}
