{"text": "So in 65h of gameplay I have been the leader the top 1 alliance of one of their servers and believe me when I say: Prepare to pay real money or waste big time. For being the leader of the best alliance in the server I got equipment for 40$ value which allowed me to get into the top 10 best players fast. I managed to group all the top players into my alliance so we kinda killed the server (we killed everyone else since it's PVP). Could easily say that the TOP 1 player paid more than 500$ If you have any question just add me :)", "appid": "1379130", "steamid": "profiles/76561198139720619", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599825600.0}
{"text": "I really wanted to like this game, I tried very hard to see what the developers were going for, but there are just way too many baffling design decisions.  The positive for me, the humor was very good, it clearly had overlap with the borderlands development.  The mission were fun, if repetitive, and I don't mean in how many times you repeat each mission.  The characters were unique in many cases, and I liked the progression style. The negative for me, first, and I can't stress this enough, the Operations are 3 player only, the rest of the coop portion is 4 player at least.  To say that makes no sense is an enormous understatement, and I feel robbed for my $29 or whatever I spent.  I could probably have read carefully and noticed this, I accept my responsibility, but me and my 3 friends expected to be able to play this content, but for no logical reason they decided just 3 for these. I hope you like doing the same things, over and over and over, because you will.  Every mission reuses the same ideas, with no variety.  Horde mode, Horde mode, Horde mode, they use this to death.   Only one presents a challenge, and then only on the hardest difficulty, the rest are trivial if you have 2 or more players.  Some missions start off extremely hard, just to become boringly easy. By the time you play this game a few weeks you will be sick to death of the movie that plays before every mission.. just one, one movie, not 3 they cycle through, and no way to turn it off. Voice chat is one of the laziest implimentations I have ever seen.  It functions most of the time, sometimes it goes crazy for no reason.  But every time a cut scene plays while you are loading or exiting the missions, all the voice chat stops, for no reason, again. A ton of information is made far to difficult to access and the menu's are extremely clunky. Lastly and far more important, this is a Free to Play Game, that's what it is, they decided to charge full price for it, and then some kind of half F2P model, but it was clearly designed with a F2P game model.  This is really unacceptable. Gearbox, you have a lot of things I like about you, but you have lost me as a fan with this one and your recent other releases.  You were close with Battleborn, I really wanted to like it, it has a lot to like, but some of the sins are unforgivable.", "appid": "394230", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985745165", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1504526400.0}
