{"text": "The first thing I want to happen when I click ''play game'' is to have access to that game ASAP so I can play it. But with Street Fighter 5 I had to read many dumb useless crap about on-line boring stuff. I even had a warning about privacy. For some reason Capcom wants to know where I live, wants to do telemetry of how I play, when I play, what crap I have downloaded to that game and OS, system... what the f.a.k.k.? I don't think I ever had to sign so much crap not even for on-line only games. To hell with that. I decided to leave it be on off-line mode just like the old times. If I want to go on a on-line match then I can just go there and click ''on-line match'', but it wasn't possible to do so during my testing because I clicked ''I don't agree with the terms''. Probably has a way to undo it, but I'm really not in the mood at the moment. When I finally managed to play this thing, shocking. Sexism was everywhere. Oh yeah, I'm a demon and everyone knows it, they even avoid me. I love it too. But when it is overused it is rather ridiculous, cringey, weird, creepy. Every woman depicted on the game is a harlot. There is not a single girl on that thing that just walks, speaks, poses or fights normally - or there's to say, like a martial artist goddess, no. They're all courtesans. They all talk like they just had it. They're just there to show sweet mega boobs. It is funny at best, instead of sexy. Obvious magnets to attract virgin dummies to play it. I heard they even had to rework Cammy's victory camera angle (to hide some parts).  Street Fighter IV and others down the series were much better at that, it was cute sexy rather than super sexual. Put too much of it and that special sex appeal will be overused and the fun will be gone. Wanna fight with hot skins boobs? Go play Dead or Alive, it is fun. Street Fighter used to have other sorts of qualities embedded. Long gone, who cares? Character design It is kinda muscley cartoonish, cool and all, but it comes at the cost of exaggeration. I can barely recognize some of the characters. Cammy's case looks severe. Tried some Cammy with Alpha's costume, but I forgot the game demands lots of DLC or something. Went to the store to see it. It is filled with DLCs everywhere for everything. Like all other fighting games, this is no longer a game but a money grabber. They arranged the packages well at least, so you don't trip too much. Want a good fighting game? I recommend Injustice 2 or even Street Fighter IV. The anime running in there is much more satisfying to see too. I didn't like SFV and I'm not wasting my time with it.", "appid": "310950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061795684", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580904000.0}
