{"text": "Game received for \"free\" as a Kickstarter bonus. Graphics and sound are cool. Character design is nice, even if sometimes it feels just like straight Castlevania ripoffs. Game plays exactly like old Castlevanias, so expect: - Slow movement and attacks - Doing everything to avoid an enemy attack and then get hit anyways and drop of stage because of the knockback - Not being able to control your jump midair - Dying to strange enemy placements the first few times you encounter them - Having to dodge some weird and big boss attacks after you deal the last hit - Trying to get to a stair midair, failing, then falling to your death - Getting hit by projectiles while on a stair because you cannot jump off it, and you move too slow - Dying to medusa heads, of course. You also get some new mechanics like: - Being able to change characters at any time, while having to manage stuff like which character you use to break the lanterns that give character specific subweapons - Having a life system where you only lose 1 stock when all your 4 characters die, but whenever one of them dies you restart at a close checkpoint without healing your other characters, so sometimes before a boss fight you're better off just killing yourself to reset your team - Playing with cool stage gimmicks like wind that constantly pushes you and makes your horrible jump even more miserable. The characters are very different from each other and the levels really leverage this system, and you always have a way to keep going even if you lost most of your team. The bosses are not great, but not bad either. Enemies are ok, you have all the classics - thing that flies in strange patterns, thing that just walks at you, thing that shoots 3 arrows from time to time, giant slow thing, thing that jumps from the water, thing that drops another thing that attacks you, etc. Even though the game is not that hard - if you keep playing, you memorize the patterns and levels, so beating it turns easier - the proccess of playing feels more frustrating than rewarding. Even the bosses are a little anticlimatic, you just attack them until they are dead. But if you liked Castlevania 1 and 3, you'll love this (probably).", "appid": "838310", "steamid": "profiles/76561198025323372", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551009600.0}
