{"text": "Over priced and outdated on launch. Mount & Blade has been the gold standard for it's genre for years, but this is a total let down. 8 Years of development it feels like a minor improvement of Warband. Combat mechanics feel ancient compared to newer, cheaper titles with smaller dev teams like Mordau. These are fundamental issues, not the expected rough around the edges early access title. Yet they are charging way too much for a game so unpolished that I'm too scared to play the campaign with all the corrupted saves I hear about.  Very disappointing.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971225098", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1586001600.0}
{"text": "I bought the Velvet Edition when it was on sale a while ago, and when I finally got around to installing it, it expected me to fill out a registration form, asking for things such as name, home address and etc. Some internet research later, turns out there was something i had to uncheck. And then after finally getting past Demo Mode, I could only play a man. With a ridiculous amount of facial modifiers. The graphics were ok I suppose, but it was like the game was trying too hard to be creepy. The voiceacting was laughable. And the combat... Well basically you smack someone over the head with a mace until they fall over. But I would definitely not recommend this game to a friend.", "appid": "7520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083963137", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1408190400.0}
{"text": "Basic tactical game. Universe is appealing, game is pretty. On the other side, game is repetitive and poor tactically. Also, unfortunately, ending is very poor. Plenty of better tactical games in the market : xcom 2, wasteland 2... (Seems pretty unfair to compare this first nice try to these masters of tactical games... sorry about that.) However, this game is great for casual gaming or to begin with turn based tactical games. I'd have loved this game with a better story and stronger gameplay. Maybe for episode 2, as everybody seems to love this game? :) 6/10", "appid": "760060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002405711", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1553083200.0}
{"text": "if you are into a game thats all about dealing damage to your own car then this might work out for you. but its so not worth paying full price. the game doesn't have any sort of goal or objective except to do trails that score you based on the amount of dents in your car. sure the physics engine in this game is pretty well done but 30$ isnt  worth it", "appid": "284160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198136308202", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1499342400.0}
