{"text": "The game is pay-to-play.  After Zenimax switched from a Subscription platform to a one time payment, they added many new items to the crown store that allows players with real money to get far ahead of those without money.  Thus, new players will find themselves playing for months just to be able to compete in PVP.  PVE, however, is a different story.  From level one, a new player can play with whomever they desire. This being said, the new Morrowind update finally drove me away from the game.  The fact that the developers tried to force their existing player base into paying another $40 after the base game fee shows that they are focused on money and not on the community.   It was the players who asked for the improvements included within the Morrowind update and it's a real shame that none of them will be able to experience their suggestions without dishing out more cash.", "appid": "306130", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063452259", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1496836800.0}
