{"text": "Have I already reviewed some Grafi games? Well, it's eems there's dozens of them. And they look al the same. 50 levels, and some physics inside this indie puzzler which has just a Christmas feeling, like - they took one of the other Grafi games and added some red and white elements. It features 100 achievements like all the other games in this series and on the other side it offers just some hours to be completed. Maybe even less than a hour if you're better than me, which is extremely possible, since I such at gaming. Since the beginning the graphics are quite crappy, they seem to be taken from some weird '90s website that you were asked to create in middle school. No instructions or tutorial are given, you're just thrown in the middle of the first level without any other button than \"play\". Eventually you'll get that you can invert gravity by clicking a circle in the bottom of the screen and the ball which will move will have to be transported upon a red platform or sort of. That's all the game. Yeah, later there will be some traps and moving platforms and such but the core of the game is the same. Apart from the extremely loud and crappy Christmas soundtrack (and I love Christmas music, but this is just a crappy instrumental traditional track taken from some 8Bit website Idk), the graphics in-game as you can see here on the Steam store page are totally cropped and well, just bad. I love minimalistic games, but these white and red things are just confusing and they all seem put there randomly. The whole thing is cheap, for sure, but it offers little entertainment and it's just a copy of a copy of tons of other physics puzzle games. I wouldn't recommend it, you can find these games for free everywhere on the Internet without having to be greeted by a huge \"merry xmas\" text every 10 seconds.", "appid": "1192500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356141989", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 15