{"text": "I stopped playing Elex a few months ago, and was hoping to resume at some point. In the end I decided freeing up 30GB from my hard drive was more important. The problem with Piranha Bytes games is that they're hit or miss. Gothic II and Risen II were extraordinary games. Risen II is one of my favorite games (which is saying a lot, considering Monkey Island was the game that defined gaming for me). I didn't finish Gothic II because of issues with the game, but I loved every second of it, too. I didn't try Gothic I, but was quite bored with Gothic III, Risen I, Risen III and now Elex. Too bad. My problem with Risen III was that they redesigned the main female characters to give her sexy attributes. I'm no prude, but I hated that they had to objectify such a well-defined character, and turn her into a soulless pin-up. I think I never forgave them for that. Ah, well. Elex is probably good enough if you like very hard games. But once you install a trainer to at least progress a bit through the game, you realize it's quite similar in spirit to Fallout 4, but without its cast of characters, and with much less to do. I may revisit the game (and my review) in the future, but for now: wait for it to be bundled, I don't know.", "appid": "411300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081340622", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590321600.0}
