{"text": "So, this heist. Well I got start saying that I did enjoy this heist at the start but after replaying a few times I gotta say... It's really boring.  Basically you enter, deactivate some fuse boxes, enter cards, wait, go to the diamond door, enter a card, wait, open diamond door, do a puzzle, get the diamond and escape. That's it. No variety, no different strategy, just nothing. You will just do the same thing over and over again... Basically you enter, alarm locks everything, hack in computer, wait, go to diamond door, wait, go to the diamond, do the puzzle correct or you will have to wait even more, drill the diamond and wait, get the diamond, wait for your ride to come and escape. This can even be more boring than stealth but I gotta say, I enjoyed more doing this heist in loud, that I did in stealth. I mean, It's still repetitive and also can be even more boring than stealth but for some reason I just preffered doing this loud. Probably because I was with friends. So if you plan to do this on loud, bring some friends.  The masks are really not my favourite and I just liked one, that being the Anubis one (Anubis <3, shall be remembered.) Patterns and materials are meh for me, since I don't care that much about them (even doe, there are some from some DLCs that I really enjoy.) Fun heist but can get repetitive real quick. If you are looking, to get a heist I recommend skipping this one and get other more worth of your money or If you don't own Payday 2, I recommend getting the GOTY edition since you will get this one and other DLCs...", "appid": "337660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198106534316", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1485604800.0}
