{"text": "Instead of having a showroom where you can buy cars and a garage where you can keep cars, you obtain new cars by driving up to cars parked on the side of the road and pressing a button and your current car switches with that one and you have a new car. This system in itself seems rather inconvenient but i figured i guess its not all bad altho i woulda prefered a way of buying cars instead of picking up random cars. Then i came across a nissan 350z. That was the first of quite a few cars that when driven up to and a switch is attempted, it takes you to the store and politely asks you for a credit card. I did prefer to buy cars but i meant with ingame money. Not locked behind dlc. Theres a difference between having dlc but keeping the stuff out of the game until someone buys the dlc, or having the stuff there and making it look like just another car but sending the player to buy it when they try to get in. Cheeky manipulative tactics. EA are a bunch of tossers", "appid": "1262560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066612518", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "60", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594296000.0}
