{"text": "TL:DR Don't waste your time, it will be hours perhaps days if you hate frustration before you can play at all, if you can get past sign in and sign up. Using my experience as a guide, you learn to grind just getting the game to launch. Requires your billing address to sign up on there site as Steam link failed. Terrible coding seems to be what I have experienced so far. The link to create your account didn't allow me to fill in the required details so an account could not be created that way. When I went to their site and manually created an account and linked it to my steam account, it did not list the games I purchased. I had to add my billing address and phone number, then manually add my keys. I am going to leave this review negative until the game delivers an experience that makes me want to come back and change this.  I would rather clean the toilet, better sense of achievement, over an hour launched and still 0 hours in game playing, the latest is you have to take the VR headset off to see your mouse when doing the setup. HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE AND GAVE UP. Getting my money back. On a good note: the experience of going through the mill of frustration I have been through so far (22 hours) should weed out anyone that isn't willing to grind a little.", "appid": "359320", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963933537", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556193600.0}
