{"text": "I was looking forward to this game until it came out and it has been a roller coaster of unfun emotion. From the servers being down all of opening weekend, to the devs resetting gold from legit accounts because some people were exploiting gold (in a game with no economy where how much gold someone has, doesn't affect you), to the balance patches that overcorrect instead of adjust. I like to think of the patches as the devs driving a car, when they realize they're going 90mph, instead of easing on the breaks they slam full force into a stop.  I think there were some legitimate fun times to be had, but anytime someone is having fun in Wolcen, the devs shut it down and don't offer an alternative. I honestly would not recommend this game.", "appid": "424370", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992667902", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582804800.0}
