{"text": "You know what?  I was playing for 7 hours non-stop hoping the game got better with the patch, and had some progress. Then as it seems, the main quest has bugged (the one when you need to board an anomaly and talk to two guys there, as I did, then I played for some time until timer have gone zero, and nothing happened. It still says \"board an anomaly, talk to guys\", and guys behave like I already done this), and I decided to restart. I come back, and you know what I see? The quest is still bugged, and I have none of my 5 exo modules, 2 of which were S class and have been wasted lots of time and effort into. I say screw this. Like, what the hell, devs? Why did I lose my modules EVEN on earlier savegame done hour and a half before the last? 7 hours of gameplay went to a freakin hole just because what? Great coding? Is it really that hard to fix your game in such a long time? Damn, earlier it was just a dull impromptu game, and now it's just a time waster made of grind and bugs which reset your progress.", "appid": "275850", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992146105", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1532433600.0}
