{"text": "Usually you get this game if you buy the complete original Doom pack and most skip this one for a good reason. This was id softwares answer to take a few fan maps and sell them to make a quick buck. Calling them master levels is just stretching it too far   Its not like all of the maps are particularly hard. Some are laughably short. Around half of them take far less than 10 minutes making it a relatively short â€œexpansionâ€ with around 20 maps.  Gameplay wise the maps rarely do the annoying teleport the player suddenly into a room full of monsters trick, instead they spam you with harder enemies.  Some of the maps are interesting and the shorter ones are usually pretty ok. They are ment to be played with a pistol start and usually give you all weapons doom has to offer very quickly. Neat! Gives a lot of verity especially when playing it with the sourceport. Setting up the sourceport is on the other hand an annoying mess, mostly due to the lack of guides and interest in the community . My biggest issue with these map packs are their even more cryptic switches, some being very hidden or generally ways to continue the map can be very abstract to find making me watch walkthroughs a couple of times after walking around for minutes being stuck. This is probably the worse than in any original doom game due the small number of maps offered here.   Some of these maps feel like 2 story expansions having their own story description from the author, some having none at all. Due you not playing the maps in a specific order this part can absolutely be ignored but itâ€™s just something I wanted to mention as I thought it was interesting to know that some of these fan made maps tried to do something bigger.   I would say skip this one unless you are a completionist. I found the hassle of setting this up with the opensource version not worth it in the end but these maps arenâ€™t as awful as some people make them appear. I still liked this one more than final doom solely because it was shorter and I didnâ€™t felt exhausted finishing this game.", "appid": "9160", "steamid": "profiles/76561197962092557", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597752000.0}
