{"text": "First off, I've really enjoyed this and I continue to play it. So why the negative review? There is a bug... a really annoying click bug.. it's been there since forever, and it keeps being brought up in twitch streams. Conversation goes like this: User - \"hey, so the click bug, you nearly fixed that?\" Dev - \"just need to get this next content update out, then we'll take a look at it. It's on the list,\" That never happens... Could you imagine if CoD had an aim bug? One that causes bullets to go vertical into the sun sometimes when you aim? The community would go bananas if the devs kept on releasing new content without addressing a fundamental flaw in an FPS (shooting and aiming), but here, in a clicker game, a frustrating click bug that happens frequently is \"not our top priority\". Make it so guys.. please, make it so. I'll change my review when this is fixed. Thanks", "appid": "612020", "steamid": "profiles/76561197967087500", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1496923200.0}
