{"text": "UPDATE: The Developer has now changed the Achievements. So, my previous 100% is no longer valid (i.e. removed by the Developer), along with the challenging difficulty that was previously needed for the \"old\" 100% Achievements.  ANOTHER UPDATE: I have finally played again & got the \"new\" 100% achievements... And all I can say is = mehhh (just keep pressing the space bar until you get 100%).... so *thumbs down* ------------------ Anyways, I hope the below (old) review of Torch Cave would still have several valid points for you, so here we go...  ------------------ I don't usually write a review, but, for this game, I felt so compelled to write one. This is one of the   games I've played in my life. So (if you can't be bothered to read everything I've written, I will sum it up for you here): Even if it was on discount / in a bundle / if I could buy it using a 90% coupon, I still won't buy it (if only I could turn back time). Some people might purchase this game for the trading cards (drops / farming), okay, that's fine (as long as you don't care about achievements at all). But, if you are anything like me (i.e. you are a pretty hardcore Achievement-Hunter), then prepare for the worst!  Yup, this (platformer) game is even more annoying / frustrating than   or   - imagine that! Sure (just like me, falling into this trap), you might say / think that you've checked it out on AStats first (and saw that it will only take you a few hours at most to get your 100% achievements). Well, you've been warned! (Good luck! This game was a waste of my time and my mental health, not to mention my strained neck and wrist). Just don't break your keyboard / mouse out of frustration.  Now, let's get down to the \"Why\".  There are so many things wrong with this game - I don't even know where to start! But here's a few worth mentioning: - The controls are so unbelievably horrible. And I repeat... Horrible! - In the game, you get this annoying \"hooking\" equipment, where you're supposed to \"hook\" from walls to walls (like Spiderman... almost!), only the hook doesn't actually hook most of the time, so you end up falling off the cliff / wall. - You can double-jump by pressing the spacebar twice, but 20 - 30% of the time you will fail even if you pressed the spacebar twice.  - The background music (especially if you are a musically-talented person like myself)... gosh...!! You can hear the drums looping and overlapping (out of sync) with another music or something that sounds like music (or God knows what?!)... You just keep hearing it overrrr and overrrr again, until you want to shoot yourself in the head. - The graphics are mediocre at best. If the above doesn't give you enough frustration as it is, fear not! Once you progress a little further in the game, you will encounter several new objects and/or functions (such as falling floors, ghost / invisible floors, moving books, rolling stones, shaky screen, weapons and enemies, etc).  If you don't already know the difference between a game that is \"super-challenging\" and a game that is \"outright frustrating\", well at least you'll learn / get something out of this game. (Please forgive my dry sense of humour, or my sarcasm rather - I just obtained my 100% achievements, and my head is just about to explode). Anyways, if, after reading my review, you still want to buy this game, for whatever reason, or if you have already bought it a long time ago (like myself), then the very best of luck to you my fellow-gamer(s). You've been warned! Best regards, Queen M", "appid": "501690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198140953252", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "71", "votes_funny": "16", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482494400.0}
