{"text": "It's one of those games where the developers heavily banked on the fact that everyone will be playing multiplayer... and because of that I think the game seriously lacks. Singleplayer is a grind fest and lacks depth. The core of the game is pretty grindy and I don't think most players would be playing it for more than 6 hours for enjoyment purposes. Most people who've played the game left because they didn't feel like this game was worth mastering, and now the only people who stick around are the masters. There isn't any sort of skill based matchmaking, and if there was one, matchmaking will like take a century to pair you with an opponent.", "appid": "473690", "steamid": "profiles/76561197991157860", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533643200.0}
