{"text": "I have a friend who has a child who has logged over 100 hours in this game, so I thought that if someone had logged such an awesome number of hours in a game then it must have some appeal. How wrong I was. There is very little gameplay here. Even when I was first getting into games over 25 years ago I would have thought this was a crap game. It makes me wonder about the mental capacity of my friends step-son, I hate to think something like this about the loved one of someone I am close to but it is a sad truth. If you enjoy this game then that might make me wonder about your mental capacity too. But I suppose if you are a fidgety kind of person who needs something to do with your hands then it might have some appeal, but then I might suggest that instead you doodle on a piece of paper, learn a musical instrument, or perform the all time number one favourite activity that one can do with one's hands when one has nothing better to do. More of an exercise in patience really, it's basically a free to play mobile game for little kids, but instead of being free to play on the Google play store it costs money on the Steam Store. Purchase at your own risk. 4.0/10 - Not bugged and nicely presented but has absolutely no gameplay or narrative value whatsoever.", "appid": "342580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198333010227", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493899200.0}
