{"text": "I had more fun in AC: Origin than I have in AC: Odyssey. It is 80% the same as Origin but Origin was something new they brought up to the AC franchise and I was impressed. But, the more time I spent on this game the more I realised that this is a tick-box game. I found myself going outpost to outpost to clear out.  By the time clear up the map I'm already level 89 and my story progression are only around where the protagonist found his mother. the Map is always full of question marks every time you discovered a place. Sure you can switch to the other mode to prevent that but the mission won't even show up on the map like RDR2 did. The story is alright compared to Origin. Not going in depth with the story.The expression of the characters are so bad. No emotions, I can say it's the lack of satisfaction after every outcome.I expect when Alexios or Kassandra found their mother will be so emotional and I was ready to grab a bag of crisps and watch the screen. but nothing emotional about it.(The game made up for it later but still). This is the first time they saw their mother since whenever it is. at least show some expression or emotions to it. The map is too big, not everything big is better, look at Greece that Ubi made. It's beautiful but in this such a big map you found yourself riding your horse to the location with no unexpected event. In RDR2 they can find people asking for help, you can find People robbing you. lots of encounter and Ubi didn't add these unexpected event is just a miss opportunities. The horses, MY GOD am I so pissed, After Playing RDR2 I simply can't find myself loving on Ubi's horse. Cough** Not that I like it since the first day. I know when you ride the horse it meant to be fast, and it's fast but they don't show it or you don't feel it. Not feeling it mean not intriguing therefore lead to losing patient. No patient often quickly turned into boredom. Luckily there is tons of Fast Travel. Don't get me wrong I love this game a lot still. But having the same release year as RDR2, This is simply trash. having a higher net worth than some of the reputable gaming companies this is not up to standard. Start producing a few games that can potentially be a masterpiece like Rockstar and many others instead of releasing games yearly that is not intriguing and uninspiring. Despite all those cons I am still pretty excite for the upcoming AC.", "appid": "812140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120120855", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579521600.0}
