{"text": "The positives: It was fun when it worked, it really was. It was a nice change of pace from all the jetpacks and skill based movement from more recent Call of Duty titles. The guns don't melt so the slower time to kill doesn't feel  like the one who shoots first always wins the gunfight. The killstreaks aren't as intrusive to the gameplay thus far and this helps the feeling of cheap deaths. Negatives: The gripes began when you are playing a match where everybody is quite literally on a one bar connection and the game becomes Slender man. I've played one such game and am still wondering why dedicated servers aren't a thing yet. In addition, the hit registration feels wonky, some shots that I felt I should've missed somehow hit and those that do enter a magical void. Additionally, the anticheat needs work. My friends and I searched for a game and landed in five lobbies each with a different aimbotter in a row locking on to heads and annihilating. We had to queue over and over again to find a proper game.", "appid": "696790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198112354649", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506859200.0}
