{"text": "This game needs to decide if it wants to be a FPS with roguelike elements or an RPG-building-management game. It fails at trying to combine both. I'm sure other reviewers will cover the negative aspects of this game better than me (they're all true, btw) so I'll just add this: most roguelike run-throughs take about 1-2 hours max right? You could easily spend 5-10 hours on a 'run' here. So either make it a one playthrough kind of game with high replay value or shorten the grindy resource collection and hyperspace travel elements. Oh, and fix the AI. For real.", "appid": "712190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198181591594", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597147200.0}
