{"text": "That was Ã” so close to be a big thumbs-up! It looks at first like a very ordinary idea (i.e. night shift in a convenience store). But in fact it's a fabulous one! And everything is in place for a real suspense, from the horror-movie cinematics, the thriller atmosphere, the realistic 'real-life' environment, and SO MUCH potential for multiple strange guests and other scary events! And then....  I tried to hang-in there and persevere, and for one very brief moment I must admit I was really looking for the 'alarm' button. But then....  You pretty much are left in-there guessing what to do next. And despite trying a lot to (hopefully) see the action take-off, I was left with no other choice but to conclude that I had just lost 2 hours of my time...and a few dollars. It honestly feels like an early access that was never finished. And for now, that's the only 'horror' in this game! But I really wish that the devs (or anyone else) will pick it up and bring it to it's FULL potential, because then this could really become a true gem in the very thin quality horror/thriller genre available at the moment!", "appid": "1228520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198373924597", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604145600.0}
