{"text": "Let me start of by saying that I personally absolutely love this game. It's in my top favourites, and probably my favourite RTS of all time. Let me also state that I do not (really) care about the changes made to the game to appeal to native americans. However, if you're like me and got massive nostalgia for the campaign, and mostly only play that. Do not get this game. The campaign is fundamentally broken right now. Especially the AI, half of the time the enemy AI gives up halfway through for some reason and stops doing anything. Sometimes they send villagers to their deaths and run out of food. Some of these issues are so incredibly obvious it's hard not to wonder; \"Have the developers even playtested the campaign?\". In my honest opinion, I do not think so. And that's the problem. Most issues in the campaign will be seen if you play the mission for 5 minutes. And some cutscenes don't even work correctly, they stop working 5 seconds in. You are forced to skip them to progress. It's terribly annoying. I also take a little issue with the changing of dialogue. The developers have changed campaign dialogue to be more respectable to native americans. And fair enough, but they did not put in the effort to voice it over. Most of the voice lines have been completely cut. A prominent native american character in the first campaign (blood, ice and steel) named Kanyenke was apperiantly an incorrect name or something. He has been renamed to ka:nien or something. The way they have cut the original voice lines is pretty jarring, but all in all a minor complain. Kanyenke's sister however, didn't get the same treatment. Her name is completely removed from spoken dialogue. Some cutscenes don't even make sense unless you have subtitles on. This is so dissapointing because I want my friends to try out the campaign, and I want it to make some sense. At this point, I do not recommend the game if you play for the campaign. The issues mentioned above, especially the broken AI, make the campaign incredibly boring. Untill the developers fix this issue, it'll be a negative from me. However, that's the campaign. Multiplayer works fine, at least for me and my friends. The AI needs some work there too, but it's a lot better.", "appid": "933110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198038106642", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603281600.0}
