{"text": "This is the first pack I have reviewed for Coloring Pixels. I've reviewed the main game with positive feedback. Unfortunately, I am unable to give positive feedback for Dinosaur Pack. It provides 2 hours of content which is acceptable for its price tag but it feels largely uninspired and dull. The images look like not much thought and creativity has gone into them. Coloring Pixels as a game itself is wonderful. It has so much content and a huge variety to keep you occupied. Sadly this latest pack as well as the previous pack (Marine Life) just isn't to the quality that ToastieLabs are capable of. ToastieLabs, according to their recent announcement, have acquired a professional development studio so I'd expect more higher quality content in the future. The DLC just feels like I am spending Â£0.79 for 21 further achievements and this says a lot for the quality of the pack. Achievement hunters like myself will throw away a measly Â£0.79 each month when packs are released just to get the remainder of new achievements which are showing up. I don't mind waiting maybe more than a month if this means ToastieLabs are able to put out better packs. All of the images are relatively small with the largest one being no greater than 110 pixels both directions. The pack just felt like a chore to get some achievements. Hopefully with the new development studio, this will be the last low quality pack ToastieLabs.", "appid": "1352583", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098956168", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600084800.0}
