{"text": "I know i'll be boo'd for this but when the hype and novelty wears off you'll find this game is no more than that of a mobile game, its set up so you get a big ol dopamine hit every time you hand in a chest but other than that this game doesn't have much to offer. All the reviews im seeing are \"HAHAHA funny le pirate game haha guys eat le banana\" and no one wants to speak about the actual problems of the game. The sword & gun gameplay is as flat and stale as a board and feels boring you'll find yourself going from a to be to solve a riddle or find an x mark on your map to then return to a dock to hand everything in. Rinse and repeat & yes the \"Tall Tales\" are a more intricate version of what i just mentioned, you literally just go from a to b but it has uninteresting characters spewing dialogue & at times more fighting but it doesn't mean much when the combat is just woeful. This is literally it, too often you'll find yourself just mindlessly sailing going nowhere fast. The ONLY progression in this game is cosmetics, so what is there to do when you've purchased the outfit you like best? i play with 3 friends and most of the time we were so bored we were forcing ourselves to make our own fun, we struggled to find many players & the arena lobby we joined failed to start after 30 minutes of us running around the starting lobby. We defeated the \"mighty\" Kraken twice, both times we bombarded it with cannons and it just withered away into the water after a few minutes and left little to no reward.  We all want to love this game but its nothing but a big yawn after the novelty wares off you're left with a slow, tiresome game.", "appid": "1172620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051014425", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594209600.0}
