{"text": "is probably a less accurate title than  . You play as an unfortunate pyjama-clad man trapped in his own room by the constant threat of elaborate   style death sequences and so, despite the titular warning, you have little choice to but to natter away online to 'Lucy', a malevolent and incredibly touchy spirit whose slightest agitation will result in you being stabbed to death or hung from the ceiling. The death sequences are hilariously over-gibbed. My car backed into at me five miles an hour and I literally detonated from the inside, my unidentifiable corpse looking like I'd fallen into a moshpit of bears. The main frustration of   isn't so much the trial and error repetition factor but just how long the steps themselves take. There's an unavoidable sequence that circles around finding a phone number that requires you to restart your in-game desktop, wait for a bunch of updates to install, wait for a scary crash sequence to finish, wait for a ghost to slowly crawl its way over to you, find the number in an error log, CALL the bloody number and FINALLY wait for the phone call to finish, after which you're finally free to do some guesswork, get yourself killed and repeat the entire exhausting process again.  Click the wrong thing, interrupt the sequence in any way and you die. Call the wrong number and you die. Go outside, you die. Go to sleep, you die. Tell Lucy that you don't have any hobbies, you die. Beat Lucy at a game of 'Buttons', you die. Lose to Lucy at 'Buttons', you die. Let Lucy watch you play 'Mech vs. Fruits', you die. Stand up, you die. Sit down, you die. If you like dying, boy, you'll think Christmas came around again already, let me tell you.  does manage to conjure a very solid atmosphere with its art style, audio and creepy randomised glitches that drop themselves into the online chat but it's far too drainingly rigid as a puzzle game. The achievements list hints at far more death sequences than I got to see but honestly, if I have to sit through that phone call puzzle one more time, I'll start trying to act them out myself anyway. You can see my fun with it below:", "appid": "533170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198169311898", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "165", "votes_funny": "64", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484049600.0}
