{"text": "An intimate game revealing the struggles and inner mechanics of the dev's struggling to understand their situation. I gave the game a chance and read through it, but it was strange. I was reading the developer's diary and genuinely, I wasn't expecting the experience. A lost love letter intertwined with a scattered diary left me with a tired feeling. While I can understand the grovel and push of the day to day, was something this intimate meant to be shared? Perhaps. It's not my place nor my healing to understand truly their experience, but I can genuinely say this was not worth the time and effort.  Art, yes. But one worth delicately absorbing? I don't think it's time well spent in my honest opinion.", "appid": "1115980", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041365325", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570881600.0}
